body:
PuTTY 0.71 (just released) fixes "a remotely triggerable memory overwrite in RSA key exchange, which can occur before host key verification". Time to update.

Changelog:
 These features are new in 0.71 (released 2019-03-16):

    Security fixes found by an EU-funded bug bounty programme:
        a remotely triggerable memory overwrite in RSA key exchange, which can occur before host key verification
        potential recycling of random numbers used in cryptography
        on Windows, hijacking by a malicious help file in the same directory as the executable
        on Unix, remotely triggerable buffer overflow in any kind of server-to-client forwarding
        multiple denial-of-service attacks that can be triggered by writing to the terminal 
    Other security enhancements: major rewrite of the crypto code to remove cache and timing side channels.
    User interface changes to protect against fake authentication prompts from a malicious server.
    We now provide pre-built binaries for Windows on Arm.
    Hardware-accelerated versions of the most common cryptographic primitives: AES, SHA-256, SHA-1.
    GTK PuTTY now supports non-X11 displays (e.g. Wayland) and high-DPI configurations.
    Type-ahead now works as soon as a PuTTY window is opened: keystrokes typed before authentication has finished will be buffered instead of being dropped.
    Support for GSSAPI key exchange: an alternative to the older GSSAPI authentication system which can keep your forwarded Kerberos credentials updated during a long session.
    More choices of user interface for clipboard handling.
    New terminal features: support the REP escape sequence (fixing an ncurses screen redraw failure), true colour, and SGR 2 dim text.
    Pressing Ctrl+Shift+PgUp or Ctrl+Shift+PgDn now takes you straight to the top or bottom of the terminal scrollback. 

https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/latest.html

group_name: PROCESS AND TECHNOLOGY FOR TOOLING COST ESTIMATORS
body:
11.TUBE AND PIPE BENDING
After a tube or pipe has been fabricated, it usually has to undergo post-fabrication treatments in order to be formed into a usable product. Bending is one of the most common of these processes, and it can be performed manually or by computer-controlled machines through either hot or cold forming methods. Depending on the particular bending process used, the physical and mechanical properties of the starting material may be altered, but the ultimate goal of building an industrial device for transporting gas and liquid remains the same regardless of the technique employed.
 
Tube and pipe manufacturers usually offer a variety of different basic designs, such as circular or square shapes, and there are also numerous custom forms available. Their products are frequently found in the agricultural, aerospace, construction, automotive, medical, and electrical industries. Most pipes and tubes used in these industries are fabricated from metal or plastic materials. Standard bending processes employs a range of tools and techniques, from mandrels that bend tubing as it is formed to triangulated rolling devices that work upon preformed pipes and tubes.
 
Bending Tools
 
Although many current pipe bending processes are automated and function under computer parameters, tooling remains an important concern in tube and pipe manufacturing. The ratio of tool life to tool price greatly influences the cost-efficiency of the overall bending process, so considerations of tool wear and failure are vital for optimizing production rates.
 
Selecting tool material and setup, such as the particular configurations of a mandrel, die set, or wiper, is a preparatory stage that can affect the actual bending procedure. Tooling costs can also be expensive, so evaluating the appropriate bend radius according to the application‚Äôs needs or standard sizing parameters before bending can reduce production expenses. Employing the same radius for multiple runs is another way to improve cost-efficiency.
 
Ram Bending
 
Ram bending is one of the oldest and least expensive bending methods used today. In this process, a pipe or tube is secured at two external points while a bending ram presses into the workpiece‚Äôs central axis. Power is shifted through a vertical ramming cylinder and the ram forces the tube against a pair of fixed rollers, causing it to bend around the die. Larger curves can be formed through incremental stages. Ram bending is commonly used to manufacture automobile exhaust pipes and forming electrical conduits. It is suited for applications in which a round cross-section is not required, as the lack of a mandrel and internal supports can cause deformation resulting in an oval-shaped cross-section.
 
Rotary Draw Bending
 
Rotary draw bending is the most common method used for applications requiring precise pipe diameters and a high quality finish. This method uses a die set consisting of a fixed radius forming die and a stationary counter die. The pipe or tube is drawn through the counter die, which pushes the workpiece against the forming die along the axis of the bend. Rotary draw bending can provide a high degree of accuracy because the two dies have a consistent center line radius. In addition, some draw bending machines can be programmed to repeat complex bending operations on multiple workpieces, improving the precision and uniformity of a production run. Rotary draw bending tubes and pipes are commonly used for a number of applications, including:
 
Conduit bending
Handrails
Automobile roll cages and chassis
Decorative iron work
Trailer frames
 
Ring Roll Bending
 
Ring roll bending is effective in forming tubes and pipes with large circumferences and center line radiuses. This method employs benders typically composed of three triangulated ring rolls arrayed on separate shafts. As the tubing passes between the rollers, the top roller exerts downward pressure, forcing the workpiece against the bottom rollers and causing the tube to bend. These rollers are often manually or hydraulically adjustable. Ring roll bending produces relatively uniform cross-sections with little deformation, and it is used for crafting drum rolls, appliance frames, truss pipes, and other rounded, large diameter components.
 
Mandrel Bending
 
Mandrel bending is a comparatively precise process that produces very few deformations in tubes or pipes. It is capable of bending thin materials to a closer radius than they could normally sustain without breaking or deforming due to the use of internal reinforcements. A flexible, internal mandrel is inserted into the tube shaft at the angle where the tube will be bent. This mandrel prevents the interior from unintended deformation while the workpiece is drawn through a counter bending die and a forming die set. Mandrel bending is commonly used to create exhaust pipes, intake and heat exchange tubing, and dairy tubing.

Quand l'occasion se pr√©sente, je mets √† jour ma liste de bookmarks sur le sujet :

http://www.semanlink.net/tag/ip_ir_ml_ia.html?longListOfDocs=true

C'est le cas aujourd'hui, avec un papier int√©ressant qui vient d'√™tre publi√© sur Arxiv par des Cor√©ens :

"A Deep Patent Landscaping Model using Transformer and Graph Convolutional Network"

https://arxiv.org/abs/1903.05823

(Le patent landscaping, c'est le fait de cartographier les brevets d'un domaine : c'est un peu la m√™me chose que la recherche d'ant√©riorit√©, mais quand on est en phase de R&D).

Comme source, ils utilisent des rapports de "patent landscaping" produits par l'office des brevets cor√©ens, et Google BigQuery pour l'acc√®s effectif aux brevets.

Leur travail est int√©ressant parce qu'il combine des techniques deep learning
- sur le texte (architecture dite du "Transformer", cf le papier fameux "Attention is all you need") 
- et sur les metadonn√©es (repr√©sent√©es via un Graph Convolutional Network).

Ils disent am√©liorer de 10% la m√©thode de landscaping propos√©e par Google.

Comme source, ils utilisent des rapports de "patent landscaping" produits par l'office des brevets cor√©ens, et Google BigQuery pour l'acc√®s effectif aux brevets.

Leur travail est int√©ressant parce qu'il combine des techniques deep learning
- sur le texte (architecture dite du "Transformer", cf le papier fameux "Attention is all you need") 
- et sur les metadonn√©es (repr√©sent√©es via un Graph Convolutional Network).

Ils disent am√©liorer de 10% la m√©thode de landscaping propos√©e par Google.

[WEC] 1000 Miles de Sebring : Signatech Alpine Matmut toujours aux avant-postes ! 

‚Ä¢√Ä Sebring (√âtats-Unis), Signatech Alpine Matmut s‚Äôest offert son sixi√®me podium cons√©cutif dans la cat√©gorie LMP2 du Championnat du Monde FIA d‚ÄôEndurance.
‚Ä¢Deuxi√®mes √† l‚Äôarriv√©e, Andr√© Negr√£o, Nicolas Lapierre et Pierre Thiriet reprennent les commandes du championnat pilotes. 
‚Ä¢L‚ÄôAlpine A470 n¬∞36 revient √† cinq points de la t√™te du classement g√©n√©ral avant de retrouver l‚ÄôEurope pour les 6 Heures de Spa (2-4 mai) et les 24 Heures du Mans (15-16 juin).

Arriv√©e la semaine derni√®re en Floride, l‚Äô√©quipe Signatech Alpine Matmut entamait sa d√©couverte du Sebring International Raceway d√®s samedi.
Apr√®s deux journ√©es consacr√©es √† l‚Äôapprentissage des pneumatiques Michelin et des subtilit√©s de ce trac√© mythique, atypique et bossel√©, l‚ÄôAlpine A470 n¬∞36 terminait deuxi√®me des trois s√©ances d‚Äôessais libres avant que Nicolas Lapierre et Pierre Thiriet ne la qualifient au troisi√®me rang du LMP2 jeudi soir. 
Le d√©part √©tait donn√© sous une chaleur √©crasante vendredi √† 16 heures. Premier √† l‚Äô≈ìuvre, Nicolas Lapierre faisait preuve de finesse pour conserver sa position avant de gagner une place d√®s le quatri√®me tour √† la faveur d‚Äôune belle man≈ìuvre √† l‚Äôint√©rieur du premier virage.
Pierre Thiriet s‚Äôinstallait ensuite au volant pour son double relais. Pass√© un temps troisi√®me, le Fran√ßais r√©agissait rapidement pour reprendre son bien alors que le ciel se faisait de plus en plus mena√ßant. 
Apr√®s le premier quart de course, la sortie d‚Äôune LMP1 provoquait une neutralisation. L‚Äô√©quipe faisait alors le choix de faire entrer en sc√®ne Andr√© Negr√£o juste avant que la voiture de s√©curit√© n‚Äôeffectue son apparition. Comme Pierre Thiriet, le Br√©silien doublait son relais avant un nouveau full course yellow dans la foul√©e de son arr√™t.
Alors que la nuit tombait sur Sebring, il devenait √©vident que l‚Äô√©preuve s‚Äôach√®verait une fois la dur√©e limite de huit heures atteinte. En parall√®le, Pierre Thiriet revenait en piste avant de laisser Nicolas Lapierre repartir √† l‚Äôattaque. Ses deux relais et les deux suivants d‚ÄôAndr√© NegrƒÅo permettaient aux Bleus de consolider leur deuxi√®me place √† l‚Äôamorce de l‚Äôultime heure. 

Dans les vingt derni√®res minutes, les premi√®res gouttes de pluie arrivaient et l‚Äô√©quipe r√©alisait le coup parfait en chaussant les full wet. Les efforts de Nicolas Lapierre √©taient n√©anmoins annihil√©s par la sortie de Lo√Øc Duval et l‚Äôintervention de la voiture de s√©curit√© jusqu‚Äôau drapeau √† damier. 
Deuxi√®me de sa cat√©gorie et cinqui√®me au classement g√©n√©ral, l‚ÄôAlpine A470 poursuivait toutefois sa s√©rie de six podiums cons√©cutifs tout en s‚Äôoffrant un deuxi√®me top cinq au scratch en cette Super Saison 2018-2019. 

Philippe Sinault, Team principal Signatech Alpine Matmut : "¬´ Ce week-end atypique se conclut sur une bonne op√©ration. Sebring est un circuit unique au calendrier avec ses bosses, de grosses diff√©rences d‚Äôadh√©rence, son climat extr√™mement chaud et d‚Äôimportantes variations de temp√©rature. Nicolas a r√©alis√© un excellent d√©part avant que la Jackie Chan DC Racing n¬∞38 ‚Äì notre adversaire principal ‚Äì ne rencontre des soucis. Cela a rapidement chang√© la physionomie de la course et nous avons choisi de limiter notre prise de risques. Notre strat√©gie voulait que Pierre roule assez t√¥t et il faut saluer son double relais de jour dans de telles conditions. Il nous a permis de rester dans le duo de t√™te et il s‚Äôen est bien sorti de nuit malgr√© un pare-brise sali par une autre voiture. En parall√®le, Andr√© et Nicolas ont tout donn√© pour garder les leaders √† port√©e de tir jusqu‚Äô√† ce final √©pique. D√®s l‚Äôarriv√©e de la pluie, nous avons pris la bonne option en chaussant les full wet contrairement √† nos rivaux qui avaient opt√© pour les interm√©diaires. Sans l‚Äôaccident de la TDS et la fin de course sous safety car, notre pari aurait pu payer, mais ce sixi√®me podium d‚Äôaffil√©e souligne notre r√©gularit√© et notre statut parmi les favoris au titre ! ¬ª

Nicolas Lapierre : ¬´ Il y a beaucoup d‚Äôenseignements positifs √† tirer de ce week-end, notamment en ce qui concerne la strat√©gie, les arr√™ts au stand, la bonne adaptation de l‚Äô√©quipe √† ce trac√© particulier ou encore le d√©but de notre collaboration avec Michelin. En revanche, nous avons peut-√™tre manqu√© un peu de performance quand les temp√©ratures √©taient plus fra√Æches. Je pense que nous avons cern√© le probl√®me et que nous sommes pr√™ts √† travailler sur cet aspect, mais le week-end se finit bien avec cette deuxi√®me place et notre retour en t√™te du classement g√©n√©ral chez les pilotes. ¬ª

Andr√© Negr√£o : ¬´ D√®s les essais du week-end dernier, nous avions trouv√© de nombreuses pistes pour √™tre plus performants en course. Cependant, nous √©tions moins √† notre avantage quand il faisait moins chaud, comme lors des qualifications. Tout se joue √† peu de choses, mais cela n‚Äôenl√®ve rien √† notre r√©sultat. Nous sommes toujours dans le match au classement √âquipes et nous repassons devant au classement Pilotes. J‚Äôai d√©sormais h√¢te de retrouver l‚ÄôEurope pour nos essais de pr√©paration en vue de Spa et du Mans. ¬ª

Pierre Thiriet : ¬´ Le d√©but de course n‚Äô√©tait pas √©vident avec le rythme impos√© par nos adversaires. Pendant la nuit, nous avons essay√© de maintenir l‚Äô√©cart et nous y sommes arriv√©s avant ce final o√π l‚Äô√©quipe a fait les bons choix pour sceller cette belle deuxi√®me place. Ce n‚Äô√©tait pas facile, notamment pour Nicolas qui a d√ª composer avec la pluie, mais je tiens √† saluer ce beau travail d‚Äô√©quipe durant nos deux semaines √† Sebring. Le bilan est donc positif et de bon augure avant les deux derni√®res manches de la saison ! ¬ª

[WEC] 1000 Miles of Sebring: Signatech Alpine Matmut still up front!

‚Ä¢At Sebring (United States), Signatech Alpine Matmut scores its sixth consecutive podium in the LMP2 category of the FIA World Endurance Championship.
‚Ä¢With their runner-up finish, Andr√© Negr√£o, Nicolas Lapierre and Pierre Thiriet reclaim the lead in the Drivers‚Äô Championship. 
‚Ä¢The n¬∞36 Alpine A470 is now five points from the lead of the general classification before returning to Europe for the 6 Hours of Spa (May 2-4) and 24 Hours of Le Mans (June 15-16).
  

Last week the Signatech Alpine Matmut team arrived in Florida to begin its discovery of the Sebring International Raceway.

Following two days spent learning the Michelin tyres and the challenges posed by the atypical and bumpy legendary track, the n¬∞36 Alpine A470 finished second in the three free-practice sessions prior to Nicolas Lapierre and Pierre Thiriet qualified third in LMP2 Thursday evening.

The race began in sweltering conditions Friday at 4pm. First in the car, Nicolas Lapierre held position before picking up a place on lap four with a classic overtake move at the inside of turn one.
Pierre Thiriet took over for his double stint. After some time in third place, the Frenchman regained his spot as the skies became more and more threatening. 
After the first quarter of the race, an incident involving an LMP1 car caused a full-course yellow. The team chose to put Andr√© Negr√£o in the car just prior to the intervention of the safety car. Like Pierre Thiriet, the Brazilian drove a double stint before another full-course yellow in the aftermath of his stop. 
While night fell over Sebring, it became clear the race would conclude once the eight-hour mark was reached. In parallel, Pierre Thiriet was back in action before leaving Nicolas Lapierre to go for it. His two stints and the next two of Andr√© NegrƒÅo allowed the French squad to consolidate second place as the race entered the final hour.
It began to rain in the final 20 minutes and the team made the perfect call in switching to full wets. Nicolas Lapierre‚Äôs efforts were annihilated by the incident involving Lo√Øc Duval and the safety car period just until the chequered flag. 

Second in LMP2 and fifth overall, the Alpine A470 made it six podiums in a row while claiming a second top five in the 2018-2019 Super Season.

[WEC] 1000 Miles de Sebring : Signatech Alpine Matmut toujours aux avant-postes ! 

‚Ä¢√Ä Sebring (√âtats-Unis), Signatech Alpine Matmut s‚Äôest offert son sixi√®me podium cons√©cutif dans la cat√©gorie LMP2 du Championnat du Monde FIA d‚ÄôEndurance.
‚Ä¢Deuxi√®mes √† l‚Äôarriv√©e, Andr√© Negr√£o, Nicolas Lapierre et Pierre Thiriet reprennent les commandes du championnat pilotes. 
‚Ä¢L‚ÄôAlpine A470 n¬∞36 revient √† cinq points de la t√™te du classement g√©n√©ral avant de retrouver l‚ÄôEurope pour les 6 Heures de Spa (2-4 mai) et les 24 Heures du Mans (15-16 juin).

Arriv√©e la semaine derni√®re en Floride, l‚Äô√©quipe Signatech Alpine Matmut entamait sa d√©couverte du Sebring International Raceway d√®s samedi.
Apr√®s deux journ√©es consacr√©es √† l‚Äôapprentissage des pneumatiques Michelin et des subtilit√©s de ce trac√© mythique, atypique et bossel√©, l‚ÄôAlpine A470 n¬∞36 terminait deuxi√®me des trois s√©ances d‚Äôessais libres avant que Nicolas Lapierre et Pierre Thiriet ne la qualifient au troisi√®me rang du LMP2 jeudi soir. 
Le d√©part √©tait donn√© sous une chaleur √©crasante vendredi √† 16 heures. Premier √† l‚Äô≈ìuvre, Nicolas Lapierre faisait preuve de finesse pour conserver sa position avant de gagner une place d√®s le quatri√®me tour √† la faveur d‚Äôune belle man≈ìuvre √† l‚Äôint√©rieur du premier virage.
Pierre Thiriet s‚Äôinstallait ensuite au volant pour son double relais. Pass√© un temps troisi√®me, le Fran√ßais r√©agissait rapidement pour reprendre son bien alors que le ciel se faisait de plus en plus mena√ßant. 
Apr√®s le premier quart de course, la sortie d‚Äôune LMP1 provoquait une neutralisation. L‚Äô√©quipe faisait alors le choix de faire entrer en sc√®ne Andr√© Negr√£o juste avant que la voiture de s√©curit√© n‚Äôeffectue son apparition. Comme Pierre Thiriet, le Br√©silien doublait son relais avant un nouveau full course yellow dans la foul√©e de son arr√™t.
Alors que la nuit tombait sur Sebring, il devenait √©vident que l‚Äô√©preuve s‚Äôach√®verait une fois la dur√©e limite de huit heures atteinte. En parall√®le, Pierre Thiriet revenait en piste avant de laisser Nicolas Lapierre repartir √† l‚Äôattaque. Ses deux relais et les deux suivants d‚ÄôAndr√© NegrƒÅo permettaient aux Bleus de consolider leur deuxi√®me place √† l‚Äôamorce de l‚Äôultime heure. 

Dans les vingt derni√®res minutes, les premi√®res gouttes de pluie arrivaient et l‚Äô√©quipe r√©alisait le coup parfait en chaussant les full wet. Les efforts de Nicolas Lapierre √©taient n√©anmoins annihil√©s par la sortie de Lo√Øc Duval et l‚Äôintervention de la voiture de s√©curit√© jusqu‚Äôau drapeau √† damier. 
Deuxi√®me de sa cat√©gorie et cinqui√®me au classement g√©n√©ral, l‚ÄôAlpine A470 poursuivait toutefois sa s√©rie de six podiums cons√©cutifs tout en s‚Äôoffrant un deuxi√®me top cinq au scratch en cette Super Saison 2018-2019. 

Philippe Sinault, Team principal Signatech Alpine Matmut : "¬´ Ce week-end atypique se conclut sur une bonne op√©ration. Sebring est un circuit unique au calendrier avec ses bosses, de grosses diff√©rences d‚Äôadh√©rence, son climat extr√™mement chaud et d‚Äôimportantes variations de temp√©rature. Nicolas a r√©alis√© un excellent d√©part avant que la Jackie Chan DC Racing n¬∞38 ‚Äì notre adversaire principal ‚Äì ne rencontre des soucis. Cela a rapidement chang√© la physionomie de la course et nous avons choisi de limiter notre prise de risques. Notre strat√©gie voulait que Pierre roule assez t√¥t et il faut saluer son double relais de jour dans de telles conditions. Il nous a permis de rester dans le duo de t√™te et il s‚Äôen est bien sorti de nuit malgr√© un pare-brise sali par une autre voiture. En parall√®le, Andr√© et Nicolas ont tout donn√© pour garder les leaders √† port√©e de tir jusqu‚Äô√† ce final √©pique. D√®s l‚Äôarriv√©e de la pluie, nous avons pris la bonne option en chaussant les full wet contrairement √† nos rivaux qui avaient opt√© pour les interm√©diaires. Sans l‚Äôaccident de la TDS et la fin de course sous safety car, notre pari aurait pu payer, mais ce sixi√®me podium d‚Äôaffil√©e souligne notre r√©gularit√© et notre statut parmi les favoris au titre ! ¬ª

Nicolas Lapierre : ¬´ Il y a beaucoup d‚Äôenseignements positifs √† tirer de ce week-end, notamment en ce qui concerne la strat√©gie, les arr√™ts au stand, la bonne adaptation de l‚Äô√©quipe √† ce trac√© particulier ou encore le d√©but de notre collaboration avec Michelin. En revanche, nous avons peut-√™tre manqu√© un peu de performance quand les temp√©ratures √©taient plus fra√Æches. Je pense que nous avons cern√© le probl√®me et que nous sommes pr√™ts √† travailler sur cet aspect, mais le week-end se finit bien avec cette deuxi√®me place et notre retour en t√™te du classement g√©n√©ral chez les pilotes. ¬ª

Andr√© Negr√£o : ¬´ D√®s les essais du week-end dernier, nous avions trouv√© de nombreuses pistes pour √™tre plus performants en course. Cependant, nous √©tions moins √† notre avantage quand il faisait moins chaud, comme lors des qualifications. Tout se joue √† peu de choses, mais cela n‚Äôenl√®ve rien √† notre r√©sultat. Nous sommes toujours dans le match au classement √âquipes et nous repassons devant au classement Pilotes. J‚Äôai d√©sormais h√¢te de retrouver l‚ÄôEurope pour nos essais de pr√©paration en vue de Spa et du Mans. ¬ª

Pierre Thiriet : ¬´ Le d√©but de course n‚Äô√©tait pas √©vident avec le rythme impos√© par nos adversaires. Pendant la nuit, nous avons essay√© de maintenir l‚Äô√©cart et nous y sommes arriv√©s avant ce final o√π l‚Äô√©quipe a fait les bons choix pour sceller cette belle deuxi√®me place. Ce n‚Äô√©tait pas facile, notamment pour Nicolas qui a d√ª composer avec la pluie, mais je tiens √† saluer ce beau travail d‚Äô√©quipe durant nos deux semaines √† Sebring. Le bilan est donc positif et de bon augure avant les deux derni√®res manches de la saison ! ¬ª

body:
L'√©quipe WAVE (WoMen and Vehicles in Europe) a le plaisir de vous convier le jeudi 28 mars 201 √† un atelier-coaching chez RENAULT NISSAN CONSULTING :
La transformation num√©rique du secteur automobile. Comment changer et rester zen !
Une rencontre conviviale pour √©changer sur une approche d√©complex√©e du num√©rique.
Le th√®me : Vente, marketing, communication, relation client, investissements technologiques, recrutement, gestion des comp√©tences, tous les m√©tiers des entreprises sont impact√©s par les changements d‚Äôusages et de m√©thodes li√©s au num√©rique. Lorsque les entreprises ont le sentiment de manquer d'effectifs et de moyens, la gestion du changement devient une source d'angoisse. Comment se construire une culture du num√©rique, comment d√©velopper une vision d‚Äôensemble, quels changements d√©clencher en priorit√© et comment les piloter.
Nous aborderons, lors de cet Atelier-Coaching WAVE, un panorama des diff√©rentes facettes de la transformation num√©rique applicables aux entreprises du secteur automobile et les bonnes pratiques pour les aborder sereinement.
PROGRAMME
- Qu‚Äôentend-on commun√©ment par "transformation digitale" ?

Le premier draft de la checklist pour les essais d'endurance aux claquements de porte de coffre (proc√©dure d'essai 32-01-915) et endurance aux manoeuvres des hayons motoris√©s (32-01-159) est disponible en fran√ßais et en anglais sur le Sharepoint.

Lors de la prochaine r√©union mensuelle, nous √©voquerons vos remarques sur cette checklist.

[English]
The first draft regarding checklist for back door slamming durability tests (test procedure 32-01-915) & maneuvering durability test for motorised back door (test procedure 32-01-159) is available in English and in French (see Sharepoint).

Then, a checklist will be proposed for other test procedures.

body:
Facts & Moves - March 18th 2019
(Full note attached below)

‚Ä¢	KEY POINTS: Towards Th. May's final push?
Apart from the Fed on Wednesday, one key focus of the week will again be on Brexit, with on the EU side, the EU Minister of European Affairs on Tuesday and then the EU leaders on Thursday and Friday set to discuss an extension to Article 50. On the UK side, there will be another attempt to pass May's deal. 
There are reports that discussions between the government and the DUP over the backstop have gained positive traction over the last few days. Chancellor Hammond made clear yesterday that a third meaningful vote will not happen tomorrow unless there are signs that the government can win a majority. If PM May somehow does pull it off, the UK would then ask the EU for a short extension of Article 50. If granted, it means the UK could leave the EU possibly before or shortly after the EU elections in May (until June 30th). Negotiations over a future trade agreement would then start, and a transition period until Dec. 2020 would kick in. If, however, the deal is blocked for a third time tomorrow or if the 3rd vote does not happen, the UK would have to ask for a longer A50 extension. Unless the EU declines, a series of indicative votes next week would follow in UK‚Äôs Parliament to consider alternative options which could include a Norway style or other customs agreement and a second referendum. Those indicative votes will help finding an acceptable model. EUR/GBP stands at 0.8567 at the time of writing.

ALSO of interest today: US (industrial production, consumer sentiment), Japan (trade balance), Brazil (economic activity), Romania (S&P rating unchanged at BBB-) 

Of importance this week: on Tuesday, UK average earnings in Jan. and unemployment rate in March; on Wednesday, UK inflation rate in Feb., US and Brazil monetary policy council; on Thursday, UK retail sales in Feb., US leading economic indicator, Japan inflation rate in Feb., Switzerland, Norway, UK and Indonesia monetary policy council; on Friday, France, Germany, EZ and US composite PMI in March, Russia and Colombia monetary policy council. On Thursday and Friday, European Council summit.

ONEVAL : pris en compte des sp√©cificit√©s VU
---
Bonjour

Les projets VU ont des sp√©cificit√©s qui doivent √™tre prises en compte dans ONEVAL

  *   Jalons de validation : par d√©faut, les validations VU de la vague PT1 ne sont pas cal√©es sur ABPT2 (comme en VP) mais sur PPC-6S   *   Supports de Validation : en VU, il n'existe pas et n'existera jamais de simulateur VC impossible √† d√©ployer sur nos projets. Tous les essais VC doivent donc √™tre cal√©s sur des EBC VH VC   *   Dur√©e des Essais : les essais r√©alis√©s par DETUV3 sur VSF ne sont pas de m√™mes dur√©es que les essais r√©alis√©s par DEATVF4 au TCR   *   Moyens d'Essais : certains moyens de DEATUV3 sur VSF restent pour le moment encore diff√©rents de ceux de DEATVF4 sur le TCR (exemple : EASYSLAM vs FLIPPER LOURD)

Ne pas en tenir compte dans la cr√©ation des standards peut poser √©norm√©ment de probl√®me au moment du d√©ploiement des appliqu√©s VU Pour comprendre, il faut savoir qu'un projet Mother VU compte presque 30 PVAL appliqu√©s syst√®mes ouvrants + pratiquement autant de PVAL structure ouvrants, alors qu'un projet VP liste environ 4 + 5 de ces PVAL Mettre √† jour ¬´ √† la main ¬ª l'int√©gralit√© des infos ci-dessus sur environ 50 PVAL appliqu√©s VU est extr√™mement chronophage

Pour ces raisons, il a √©t√© act√© par Val√©rie et Didier que les lignes de validation de type Essais physiques devaient √™tre d√©doubl√©es dans les PVAL standards ONEVAL, au moins pour certains PVAL Systemes  (voir * ci dessous)

  *   Le paquet de lignes 1 sera d√©di√© au VP, le 2eme sera sp√©cifique VU   *   La diff√©renciation sera document√©e dans le champs ¬´ Applicabilit√© (crit√®re) ¬ª en colonne AI      *   Pour les lignes VP, indiquer PC (Passenger Car V√©hicule)
     *   Pour les lignes VU, indiquer LCV (Light Commercial V√©hicule)   *   En vague VC, les EBC resteront document√©s en tant que Simulateur (UNIT) pour le VP mais en jours d'essais sur VH pour le VU   *   Les dur√©es des essais seront document√©es √† partir du fichier Excel cr√©√© par Jean Luc GNONLONFOUN et archiv√© sur notre SharePoint      *   avec les dur√©es de r√©f√©rences VP document√©es par J-Luc
     *   et avec les dur√©es d'essais fournies par DEATUV3 pour le VU, sur la partie droite du m√™me tableau   *   En vague PT1 , les jalons de validations resteront document√©s sur ABPT2 pour le VP, mais seront cal√©s sur PPC-6S sur le VU   *   (*) Pour simplifier avant fin Mars, il est possible de ne pas effectuer la duplication sur les PVAL suivants      *   ECDO, sp√©cifique VU
     *   PSD, sp√©cifique VU
     *   Hayon motoris√©, sp√©cifique VP
     *   L√®ve-vitre : Essais r√©alis√©s par DEATVF4 et donc 100% coh√©rent avec processus idem VP      *   Toit Ouvrant : sp√©cifique VP
     *   PLC classique : sp√©cifique VU
     *   PBAR classique : sp√©cifique VU
Elle doit donc √™tre r√©alis√©e en priorit√© sur Capot, Hayon manuel et Porte LAT

Cordialement
Eddy SZATAPSKI



DEA-VU - Sce DEA-VUB (65135)
API : VSF 0G1 0 32
Tel. : +33 1 76 83 22 09
Mob. : +33 6 28 92 31 14 www.groupe.renault.com<http://www.groupe.renault.com/>


Confidential C

En compl√©ment de Skype et de Yammer en remplacement des mails pour les discussions "plus ou moins persistantes", ne faudrait-il pas ajouter MS Teams, qui apporte son lot de fantaisies. J'avoue que la diff√©rence avec Yammer est subtile, mais il me semble que, comme le nom l'indique, il est indiqu√© pour des √©quipes qui trouvent l√† tout √† la fois un forum de discussion structur√© (on peut cr√©er des groupe √† l'envi) et tout ce qu'il faut pour stocker et partager de l'information, des compte-rendus de r√©union, planifier des actions (√† chaque √©quipe / groupe de discussion, on peut associer tous les outils tels que SharePoint, Bloc Notes, Plan)... Bref, un "plateau virtuel" pour une √©quipe. Qu'en pensez-vous? Quelles sont les recommandations d'utilisation? Je suis moi-m√™me en phase d'exp√©rimentation de Teams, mais je n'ai pas encore de conclusion √† partager...

[[tag:31444568]] [[tag:31444569]]

Hi Team,

Please let me know the feasability/your inputs of the following points to be handled in our Model checker scripts.

1. MC Scripts to handle simulink data dictionary variables, Model workspace variables and base workspace variables

2. For example (Scenario shared by Florian) - "Some models are sharing a configuration reference object for which the sample time is TS. If TS is defined in the sldd or in the base workspace, all models linked to the configset object will use this value. Except if the parameter is directly defined in the Model Workspaces which have precedence. => First, the script must check if the data is defined in the Model Workspace, the if it is not, check the value in the sldd/base workspace depending of the kind of the model."

body:
(OYAK RENAULT BURSA TURKEY)
First step of AILN Bursa Multi Part shipment project achieved
A ceremony to celebrate this event with the participation of Olivier GRISELIN and DLO&AILN team members has been organized.

One of the breakthrough action plan for AILN Bursa for 2019 is to achieve multi part shipment with B98 Oran painted body containers to optimize transport costs. Shipping FR and RR Bumpers inside body containers from week 11 is the 1st step of this project.
This project start up is realized thanks to an agile philosophy working way and a collaborative relationship between AILN , Oran customer and DEAP.

Buna dimineata,

1. In sfarsit, dupa o saptamana, am primit si noi informarea despre modificarile aparute pe traseul Prundu Depou- Complex 2 - Titu.
2. Vineri 14 Martie, soferul este nevoit sa opreasca pe A1 pentru a recupera componentele desprinse din autobuzul aflat intr-o stare deplorabila.
3. In cele din urma, temperaturile de primarava, reusesc, sa ne ia prin surprindere, Luni 18 Martie. In jurul orei 16:15 cand oamenii intra in autobuz...+30¬∞C. Oare acestea sunt conditiile optime de calatorie pe un traseu de aproximativ 90Km?  

Oare cate lucruri vor mai trebui sa se intample pentru a se rezolva problemele cu siguranta si confortul calatorilor???

Pentru cƒÉ, de»ôi atletismul este un sport individual, el nu se poate dezvolta dec√¢t dacƒÉ vom alege sƒÉ "alergƒÉm" √ÆmpreunƒÉ, nu unii √Æmpotriva celorlal»õi! A»ôadar, vƒÉ a»ôteptƒÉm alƒÉturi de noi, chiar pe 1 Mai 2019, √Æncep√¢nd cu ora 8:30, pentru a lua parte la cea mai frumoasƒÉ zi de 1 Mai petrecutƒÉ √ÆmpreunƒÉ cu prietenii »ôi colegii din atletism. Como dice [[user:1614253214]], no conocemos el valor de la X, pero sabemos (m√°s o menos) qu√© hace Microsoft para calcular el valor de la X: si hay poco espacio en el disco*, y no hemos usado recientemente el fichero**, se eliminar√° la copia local de los archivos "disponibles localmente", y por tanto, estos archivos dejan de ocupar espacio en el disco duro del PC (el enlace al fichero sigue estando disponible en la carpeta OneDrive). En otras palabras, s√≥lo los archivos que marquemos como "siempre disponibles" permanecen "para siempre" en nuestro PC (y por tanto, ocupan espacio). Este matiz tan s√∫til marca la diferencia entre archivos "siempre disponibles" y archivos "disponibles localmente". 

* no sabemos cuando considera Microsoft que hay "poco espacio en disco"
** no sabemos cuando considera Microsoft que un fichero ha estado "mucho tiempo sin usarse"

J'avoue que mis √† part en le faisant expr√®s, je ne vois pas trop le risque.
D√©j√† aujourd'hui, il est possible d'√©crire en toute lettre dans un document "ULTRA CONFIDENTIEL" m√™me quand le document ne parle que du beau temps! L'incoh√©rence marquage/niveau de confidentialit√© r√©elle n'est pas nouveau. Surtout que les outils pr√©c√©dents √©taient loin de r√©pondre √† ce besoin.

Les options de chiffrement issues de ce menu sont bien du AIP, le document est prot√©g√© conform√©ment √† ce que demande l'utilisateur. Si l'utilisateur met VOLONTAIREMENT une √©tiquette puis va VOLONTAIREMENT modifier les options de chiffrement, alors oui, il se retrouve avec une √©tiquette qui ne correspond pas forc√©ment aux options voulues. Mais il le fait totalement expr√®s dans ce cas. D'autant que ce menu n'est pas visible sur le ruban affich√© par d√©faut, il faut naviger pour aller dessus.

De surcroit je rappelle que pour chaque niveau A,B,C, toutes les possibilit√©s de chiffrement (ou non chiffrement) sont accessibles dans la barre AIP.

body:
The All-new Clio won its first award!
The general public elected it as the best Production Car of the 2019 Geneva Motor Show at the Auto Plus / RTL / Turbo Grand Prix. Olivier Brosse, Program Director of the New Clio received the prize. 
A great reward for the Groupe‚Äôs iconic city car, which won by a majority of 56% of the votes the battle between 8 production models presented at the show. 

After 30 years, 2019 marks the beginning of this fifth generation, determined to remain the leader in its segment. Clio will be able to count on its spacious and innovative interior, with the widest screens in its category coupled with the brand new Easy Link multimedia connected system. It is also a pioneer for Renault and for the segment in many aspects. New Clio inaugurates the new E-TECH hybrid technology and advanced driving assistance (first step towards the autonomous vehicle)

"This is the first award for this new Clio and all the teams that have worked to create the best Clio ever. We are pleased to see that this internal enthusiasm is also widely shared and amplified by the public and many fans. It is a true sign of confidence in Renault and New Clio, which inaugurates a range of future products that are connected, electric and autonomous. "says Olivier Brosse.

New Clio inaugurates the new E-TECH hybrid technology and advanced driving assistance (first step towards the autonomous vehicle)

"This is the first award for this new Clio and all the teams that have worked to create the best Clio ever. We are pleased to see that this internal enthusiasm is also widely shared and amplified by the public and many fans. It is a true sign of confidence in Renault and New Clio, which inaugurates a range of future products that are connected, electric and autonomous. "says Olivier Brosse.

Edouard.

body:
The Most Productive Thing You Can Do With 10 Free Minutes Alone
It‚Äôs probably the opposite of what you expect

Matthew Kent
Dec 1, 2018


We all get the same 24 hours each day.

Some of it is taken up by sleep, some of it by previous commitments, but there is still plenty of time to get important work done.

Obviously if you can, you want to set aside big chunks of time for working on the things that move you closer to your most important goals. But often there are little slivers of time throughout the day that are too small to engage in deep work. What should you do with them?

I have at least three good answers but I think that one is the overwhelming winner. First, the honorable mentions:

Exercise
It‚Äôs no secret that developed nations are becoming less healthy and more sedentary.

It‚Äôs also important to remember that you are a body and not just a brain, and that the capability of your brain isn‚Äôt entirely disconnected from the state of your body.

If you have 10 minutes to spare, there are worse things you could do than some calisthenics.

Reading
I read 59 books last year and so far this year I‚Äôve read 50 (as of 11/28/18). It‚Äôs pretty safe to say that I wouldn‚Äôt be writing on Medium without my reading habit.

Writing requires input and output. You need to feed your mind and then use it to produce valuable thoughts. The higher quality your inputs, the higher quality your outputs.

Reading books is a great way to increase the quality of your inputs. A spare 10 minutes every day can lead to an additional 15 books every year, even at fairly average reading speeds.

Imagine how much you could grow by reading an additional 15 books a year.

The Real Winner
While I‚Äôm completely sold that you should be adding exercise and reading to your list of daily habits, I actually have a different suggestion for what you should do with 10 spare minutes alone:

Nothing.

That‚Äôs right, I think the most productive thing you can do if you find yourself with ten minutes to spare is to do nothing.

Now, obviously I need to do some explaining, and I‚Äôll start by clarifying what I mean.

I don‚Äôt mean that you need to lie perfectly still and not move a muscle, I just mean that you give your brain a chance to relax for a bit. That you give your mind time to wander.

Every athlete knows that rest is one of the most critical components of elite performance, but no one seems to bother to apply this lesson learned from the body to the mind.

Your brain essentially has two modes that it can operate in. Psychologists often call these modes system one and system two, taking their cues from Nobel prize winner and author of Thinking, Fast and Slow, Daniel Kahneman.

System one is effortless and swift. It‚Äôs what you might call intuition. System two is slow and effortful and where real thinking happens. If you were walking next to me and I suddenly asked you what 228 divided by 38 was, you would probably stop in your tracks. This is an outward expression of the inward switch from system one to system two.

Neuroscientists call these two modes diffuse mode and focus mode. Diffuse mode is something like a pinball machine: there‚Äôs a lot of mental space for your thoughts to bounce around and make connections. Focus mode is like a bowling lane with bumpers. Your thoughts are locked in on one goal and there‚Äôs not a lot of wiggle room.

Neither of these is better than the other and they both have their uses, but the important point is that you are most effective when you are able to alternate between these two.

Deep work happens in focus mode, but it is quite taxing. Sooner or later you need to let your mind relax again. Not only does this rest allow you to be more effective with your next focused session, it also allows you to be more creative as it gives your mind time to make connections that you miss while in focus mode.

This is why many people find the famous pomodoro technique effective, it provides a system for alternating focus and diffuse mode.

Real vs. Fake
Here‚Äôs a key point though: your mental rest needs to be real rest.

There are lots of examples of you ‚Äúchecking out‚Äù or ‚Äúunwinding‚Äù that are counter-productive.

For instance, what do most people do with ten free minutes? They check their phones. In some cases this is even somewhat justified, they have businesses that in part revolve around their ability to connect socially.

Here‚Äôs the problem though, when you are looking at your phone (or any screen), your mind is not free to wander. Instead, as MIT professor and Harvard alum Sherry Turkle points out in her excellent book Reclaiming Conversation, your attention is captured and divided.

It‚Äôs almost like a third mode for your brain to exist in has been created: reactive mode. In reactive mode you have the illusion of control, but your attention is more often than not under the control of an algorithm. It sort of looks like focus, but there‚Äôs no deep thinking. It sort of looks like mental relaxation, but your mind is not free to wander and proactively determine what it will think about. You are stuck reacting to someone else‚Äôs agenda.

There are many ways to let your brain relax and your mind wander, but one of the most classic is going for a walk.

There are good reasons behind this. If you are a knowledge worker, chances are that you were quite stationary during your bouts of focus. A walk is a good opportunity to add some much needed movement to your routine. There‚Äôs nothing about the mechanics of executing a walk that requires any concentration, and the while some of the visual stimuli you encounter might be interesting, there is nothing that demands your attention the way a screen does.

Of course, a walk is just one method. You can lie on your bed and throw a football at the ceiling if that is your thing. You can pace back and forth as I often do if you wish.

Whatever you do, you will be more effective and more creative if you regularly give your mind time to wander.

Final Thoughts
If the title of this post was at all appealing to you, chances are you are too busy for your own good. You need some time for your mind to unwind.

Fortunately, there might already be time in your busy schedule that can be repurposed and used intentionally and the best part is, you don‚Äôt even have to do anything. Stop scrolling and spend some time idly daydreaming.

Sometimes doing nothing really is more productive than doing something.

Dear SMSN,
If you receive a invitation to switch from ACE1 to ACE2, please decline it. Indeed, there is issue with AMESIM software. The impacted simulations are: AC loop, Thermal underhood and underbody. Until this issue is solved, please do not update to ACE2. Thank you in advance for your awareness.
Best regards,
Elise

Best regards,
Elise

body:
RUN R3 CC82 s1912
---
Buenos d√≠as

Paso el resumen del run del 18/03/2019

  *   No se ha introducido ninguna pieza de R3 por el ramal B por la aver√≠a de la OP 20B. Ha estado mantenimiento toda la ma√±ana.   *   No se han reintroducido las 40 piezas R3 DET a la salida de la OP100 porque hab√≠an sido chatarreadas.   *   Debido a las numerosas aver√≠as que ocurrieron simult√°neamente al run, no pudimos tener el soporte que hubi√©ramos querido para realizar los ajustes necesarios, por lo que se har√°n el parada programada.

  *   Reintroducci√≥n 15 piezas DET del run anterior por OP1760 hasta CF.

     *   4 Chatarras:
        *   1 en la c√©lula de la OP1760 B  del chanfering por mala cogida del robot al sacarla de la m√°quina (garra 2) de chanfering.         *   2 en la OP200B por rotura de herramienta.
        *   1 vista en control final con la pletina de la cara 500 rota.      *   Defecto de lectura de RFID en Triselective. No reconoce correctamente el DET. Se pone en paso a trav√©s. [User:1678576581:rafaelblanco-perez-extern] lo revisar√°.      *   2 Atranques por desatornillado de la etiqueta Balluf en la cabina de descarga del p√≥rtico de la OP200.      *   OP 240C. Se introduce DET por primera vez en esa m√°quina. Defecto: "se excedi√≥ la medida excedente m√°xima" en alrededor de 5 piezas. Se borra y arranca; se midi√≥ rugosidad y salieron OK.      *   3 Atranques en el m√≥dulo de secado de la lavadora OP porque no detecta la pieza. Se sacan las piezas a mano.      *   Atranques repetidos en la mesa de giro posterior a la Jenoptik. [User:1678576581:rafaelblanco-perez-extern].


     *   5 piezas a gravimetr√≠a a cargo de [User:1634423432:jose-pedrocasas-renones]      *   6 piezas llegan al control de estanqueidad y dan malas de la prueba de agua. El turno de tarde se encarga de limpiar el √∫til de la m√°quina y de reintroducir las seis piezas.

  *   Introducci√≥n de 153 piezas R3 DDT por la carga por el ramal C, controladas por nosotros hasta la OP95. Siguen hacia delante por la l√≠nea.

OP10

  *   Problema de detecci√≥n de algunos c√°rteres R3 debido a que la iluminaci√≥n de la c√°mara estaba desconectada. Intentamos acceder al controlador pero pide contrase√±a y usuario y los desconocemos. [User:1683392005:jose-mariagarcia-duque-extern] se encarga de hablar con el proveedor.

OP15

  *   Tras indexar, las balluf no son atornilladas correctamente. Falta una de las medias-lunas que, como se puede ver en la foto est√° sobre la carterizaci√≥n, y las piezas se mueven demasiado al alcanzar el tope.


OP20C

     *   [User:1678576581:rafaelblanco-perez-extern] se ha encargado de arreglar el tope de la entrada de la OP20C.

     *   El volum√©trico del posicionador transversal 2+5 da fallo de bridaje varias piezas al comienzo del run por valores excesivos (en torno a -700). Adem√°s superaba los -50 de fuga al abrir. Despu√©s de varias piezas los valores de bridaje van bajando y deja de dar fallo. En torno a 40 piezas despu√©s vuelve a dar fallo por no llegar al valor de referencia al abrir (-430 /430). Se bajan los valores de referencia repetidamente porque sigue fallando, hasta llegar a un valor de referencia de -280 / 280 al final del run. Nuestra sugerencia es que hay que cambiar el cilindro de dicho posicionador transversal 2+5 porque no hemos llegado a ver repetitividad de los valores tras 8 horas de run. [User:1674054618:raulrmadrid-ortega], @VIELBA-CUEVAS [User:1631461674:josevielba-cuevas].

     *   Apareci√≥ dos veces un defecto debido a la longitud de herramienta. Aunque permiti√≥ borrarlo y arrancar. Investigo de qu√© se trata y si es particular del R3 o no.


     *   Defecto de presencia pieza a la salida. Los R3 no llegan al tope de salida porque no tienen tracci√≥n suficiente. (m√°s de 5 veces). Hay que ajustar la manutenci√≥n de salida, bien sea el tope, las gu√≠as o la altura de los rodillos. [User:1674054618:raulrmadrid-ortega], @VIELBA-CUEVAS [User:1631461674:josevielba-cuevas].


OP40C

  *   Un fallo porque la barra no permite girar a la pieza por completo sobre la mesa de giro una vez indexada. Se limpia el detector bajo el camino de rodillos de la m√°quina y no vuelve a aparecer el defecto.


OP50C

  *   La pieza se queda atrancada en el puesto 2 cuando va hacia el puesto 1. (2 veces). Se entra y se mueve la pieza manualmente.


OP60C

  *   Defecto solapamiento pieza. Falsa alarma, pues se comprueba que las piezas est√°n bien colocadas sobre la horquilla. Falla continuadamente porque los l√°seres est√°n muy cr√≠ticos. @PRIETO-DIEZ [User:1631510201:rubenprieto-diez] se encarg√≥ de moverlos ligeramente para continuar con el run, pero necesitamos que se haga un seguimiento de que funciona bien con R4 y que da fallo cuando las piezas est√°n mal colocadas.


  *   La pieza se queda atrancada en el puesto 2 cuando tiene que ir al 1.

OP70C

  *   Un defecto volum√©trico de pinza 1+5 en desbridaje. Se borra y arranca y no se vuelve a repetir.   *   Un solapamiento pieza por mala cogida de la pieza por la horquilla de carga. En principio no parecen requerir ninguna acci√≥n de momento.

OP80C

  *   Defecto de presencia pieza a la salida. Los R3 no llegan al tope de salida porque no tienen tracci√≥n suficiente. (m√°s de 5 veces). Hay que revisar la manutenci√≥n de salida, bien sea el tope, las gu√≠as o los rodillos. [User:1674054618:raulrmadrid-ortega], @VIELBA-CUEVAS [User:1631461674:josevielba-cuevas]. Muy similar a lo que ocurre en la OP20.   *   Las etiquetas Balluf de las piezas rozan con la antena a la entrada de la 80C. Probablemente haya que ajustar un poco las gu√≠as o la antena.


  *   Defecto de control de placaje. Apareci√≥ continuamente. Se limpia la superficie de apoyo de la pieza y dej√≥ de aparecer.


OP95

  *   Fallo de lectura de RFID a la salida. Se necesita ajuste de la antena o de las gu√≠as.   *   Las Balluf chocan con un tope a la entrada del volteador. Se deshabilita el volteador.

Gracias

Un saludo

Enrique Berrio Galindo
CAMI  Mecanizado C√°rter Cilindros

Confidential C

Re bonjour, 
dernier outil mis √† disposition : 
dans l'onglet MARS du SharePoint, vous pouvez d√©sormais trouver la derni√®re version de MARS. 

Onglet projet : celui qu'on documente :
Cette version est bas√©e sur SESAM_CHASSIS_20_20 , dont elle reprend toutes les fiches. Il y a aussi un acc√®s direct au fiches par lien hypertexte.
Sur chaque fiche projet, on peut mettre plusieurs lots , ce qui permet d'assurer la coh√©rence (exemple : Emboutissage + Soudage +  Montage. L'objectif n'est donc pas d'avoir 1 MARS par PFI. On veut 1 MARS pour plusieurs PFI qui travaillent ensemble . La documentation se fait par chaque pilote (trier par pilote) et pour chaque jalon. 
Les codes de chaque couleur a √©t√© chang√© pour √™tre plus facilement interpr√©table : 
 NC : apparait lorsqu'il n'y a pas de lot / Bleu : On a d√©cid√© de ne pas faire / Vert : R√©sultat OK/ Gris : D√©marr√© / Orange : Pas d√©marr√© / Rouge : R√©sultat NOK . la documentation se fait comme avant, mais le calcul est plus rapide. 

Onglet Synth√®se : vision des r√©sultats 
C'est vous qui documentez le jalon que vous voulez voir, et MARS calcule automatiquement l'avancement par rapport aux fiches SESAM attendues √† ce jalon. Il vous donne la situation de chaque lot, mais aussi la situation de chaque processus , et celle de chaque livrable. 

J'ai mis un exemple pr√©-rempli pour que vous puissiez voir ce que √ßa donne comme r√©sultat 
Ce nouvel outil est en test. Si vous voulez l'utiliser , allez-y , et faites moi parvenir vos remarques et vos fichiers MARS svp . 


"En avant MARS" ( d√©sol√©‚Ä¶.je n'ai pas r√©sist√©) 

St√©phane

Hello everyone,

We resolve some bugs and we deploy new functionalities in production, today :)

Now you can find : 
- a new box called "In-transit with ETA in the past". I presented you this box during our meeting on Monday.
- you can find in the pop-up of refresh data, the date and hour of every API (see screenshot)
- back order qty goes into back orders box when the day is past (no matter what time of the day) - we still have to consider the hour of day D but it will be done when we will deploy hourly granularity.


Do not hesitate to test these new functionalitites and if you have questions, we will share them together during our meeting on Friday,

Emmanuelle

Reminder : https://eu-jb2e-prodn.nmcorp.nissan.biz/appv-ui/app

Autre point concernant AIP, Guillaume...
C'est une co√Øncidence mais une utilisatrice m'a fait remarquer cet apm que dans powerpoint (comme word et excel), on pouvait utiliser directement l'option "Autorisations personnalis√©es" du menu AIP, sans passer par les options  "No marking N", "Internal I" etc. (voir PJ)
Effectivement, la m√™me fen√™tre s'ouvre pour positionner les droits, personnes autoris√©es et date. Et les droits s'appliquent bien quand le doc est diffus√©, pas de soucis. Mais l√† non plus, pas de mise √† jour du marquage dans la barre PMI, donc si on avait "... \ Accessible to everybody", ce libell√© reste alors que le document est en fait en acc√®s restreint.
Pour moi, il faut soit supprimer cette option (puisqu'elle existe pour chacun des niveaux de confidentialit√©), soit mettre √† jour le libell√© PMI avec "... \ Accessible with personalized permissions".

L√† encore, rien de dramatique. Tu vas sans doute dire (ou penser) que je pinaille, mais c'est une question de coh√©rence : √ßa risque d'induire des utilisateurs en erreur, ou pire, ne pas leur donner confiance dans cette fonctionnalit√© pourtant tr√®s utile.

Pour moi, il faut soit supprimer cette option (puisqu'elle existe pour chacun des niveaux de confidentialit√©), soit mettre √† jour le libell√© PMI avec "... \ Accessible with personalized permissions".

L√† encore, rien de dramatique. Tu vas sans doute dire (ou penser) que je pinaille, mais c'est une question de coh√©rence : √ßa risque d'induire des utilisateurs en erreur, ou pire, ne pas leur donner confiance dans cette fonctionnalit√© pourtant tr√®s utile.

body:
Facts & Moves - March 19th 2019
(Full note attached below)

‚Ä¢	KEY POINTS: RUB shows no sign of abating 
Once again, it was a relatively quiet day in terms of data release. The rally in EM currencies showed no sign of abating overnight, with the RUB and INR being the best performers over the last days.  Positioning for a dovish Fed tomorrow may be one reason but this must also be judged in the light of the support by OPEC and Russia to extend oil production cuts and, perhaps more importantly, the seasonal fillip from corporate tax and VAT payments over the next ten days (repatriation of FX), estimated around EUR 25bn.
Separately, Feb. industrial production was released today, showing an acceleration of activity. The gauge increased by 4.1% YoY, a record high pace since mid-2017. Manufacturing drove the growth of a broad industrial production gauge having recovered to 4.6% YoY after a slowdown over last three months. Among the industrial drivers, one can highlight food production, gasoline, diesel fuel and production of construction materials. At the same time, mining segment performed strongly (5.1% yoy) in spite of implementation of the OPEC+ agreement since Q1-19.

ALSO of interest today: US (USD selling), UK (Brexit, employment data), Romania (current account), South Korea (Minutes of last MPC), Oil prices

body:
China is itself a new region from April;
AMI scope expanded to Pacific and ASEAN
----------------
In order to accelerate the Group transformation, boost the profitability of operations and develop growth in new markets, Groupe Renault announces the following appointments in its Regions.
 
As of April 1, 2019

Philippe Buros, currently SVP Market Area France, is appointed chairman of the Europe Region. He reports to Olivier Murguet, EVP, Sales and Regions. Philippe Buros is a member of the Renault Management Committee.
 

Ivan Segal, currently managing director of the Renault Iberia Cluster, is appointed SVP Market Area France. He answers to Philippe Buros and becomes a member of the Renault Management Committee.
 

To develop growth in China and better meet customers‚Äô needs in this key market as part of the Drive The Future strategic plan, Groupe Renault is creating a China Region:

Fran√ßois Provost is appointed SVP, chairman of the China Region. He reports to Olivier Murguet, EVP Sales and Regions. Fran√ßois Provost is a member of the Renault Management Committee.

Korea, Japan, ASEAN countries and Australia are grouped in the Africa-Middle-East-India (AMI) - Pacific Region, of which Fabrice Cambolive is SVP and chairman.

je me suis aussi int√©ress√© √† la question, √† l'occasion d'un projet de TIPE avec ma fille ;-), il y a quelques ann√©es.
J'ai une mini carte de mesure de Ph Atlas Scientific ($40, de m√©moire, ramen√©e de Brooklyn dans ses bagages par une amie ;-), qui fonctionne bien avec Arduino et une sonde pH pas ch√®re d'aquarium.

Il faut du courant alternatif, et d'autres choses que je ne ma√Ætrise pas ...

J'ai regard√© ton typon. Oui, c'est tout √† fait faisable en gravure √† l'anglaise. Il suffira de vectoriser le fichier bmp, pour avoir des lignes support de fraisage (d√©tourage des pistes d'isolation), et un fichier de trous de per√ßage.

Il semble qu'on ne peut pas se contenter de mesurer simplement la r√©sistance entre 2 √©lectrodes inox, gr√¢ce √† une entr√©e analogique de l'Arduino, car des ph√©nom√®nes de polarisation des √©lectrodes faussent les mesures. Il faut du courant alternatif, et d'autres choses que je ne ma√Ætrise pas ...

J'ai regard√© ton typon. Oui, c'est tout √† fait faisable en gravure √† l'anglaise. Il suffira de vectoriser le fichier bmp, pour avoir des lignes support de fraisage (d√©tourage des pistes d'isolation), et un fichier de trous de per√ßage.

Tu as aussi d'autres moyens si tu veux le faire √† la maison :
Imprimer le typon (imprimante laser) sur un papier sp√©cial, faire un transfert thermique au fer √† repasser du toner vers le cuivre. Puis attaque chimique en ayant achet√© du perchlorure de fer, ou une mixture eau oxyg√©n√©e et acide chlorhydrique. Attention, pr√©cautions √† prendre et savoir comment manipuler les produits chimiques, notamment les acides et l'eau ...
Je suis √† ta disposition si tu veux des pr√©cisions.

body:
Parteneriatul cu Prima Evadare continua si in acest an, intr-adevar. Ieri am lansat catre tot Groupe Renault Romania invitatia de a va alatura din nou TeamRenault pentru a participa la aceasta competitie. Ca si pana acum, regulile de inscriere sunt urmatoarele:
- fiecare participant se inscrie pe site-ul oficial al competitiei - pentru a putea primi numar oficial
- cu dovada platii, se pot inscrie intern pentru primirea unui echipament profesional - tricou si pantalon
Detaliile le gasiti in email-ul trimis de pe Comunicare Romania.

Proiectul este derulat tot sub marca Renault, iar persoana desemnata sa va raspunda intrebarilor este [[user:1629065458]]. Evident, va stau si eu la dispozitie pentru orice nelamurire.

Va asteptam la start! :)

body:
Acciones Gaindu 19/03/2019
---
Buenos d√≠as,

En la 8340 se ha realizado durante la noche de hoy 2 acciones a se√±alar:

  *   Cambio muelles + calzo de los mismos en elevador--> No se notan diferencias en los valores de estanqueidad pero, es una acci√≥n para alcanzar a la presi√≥n adecuada de cierre ya que, antes de la intervenci√≥n la fuerza aplicada era de 1200kg y, actualmente es de 1900kg (aprox), fuerza para lo que est√° dimensionado.


  *   Fijaci√≥n cierre lateral bomba agua--> De un inicio, el cierre lateral F300 dispon√≠a de 2 peque√±as flotabilidades, placa entera y cierre en el chafl√°n de la bomba de agua. Actualmente, una de ellas, la de la placa, se ha fijado (ver im√°genes, se√±alada en rojo) ya que provocaba la deformaci√≥n de la junta (en la OP295_CC82est√° fija).

Cuando se entraba a tocar/limpiar en la estaci√≥n, √©sta volv√≠a a su origen con lo que se comportaba bien de nuevo hasta la siguiente "deformaci√≥n".

Con esta acci√≥n, se han conseguido recuperar todas las piezas no conformes generadas en el turno de tarde pero, ser√≠a de gran ayuda continuar con el batonaje para constatar que es la soluci√≥n definitiva.


En la OP1740, la flotabilidad comentada arriba no existe...esto implica que el problema venga de otro foco que no conocemos.... Ma√±ana estar√° de nuevo Gaindu, para observar el funcionamiento de la OP8340 tras las modificaciones y para, comenzar su intervenci√≥n en la OP1740, ya sea por la tarde mirando o por la noche interviniendo.

Os mantengo al tanto en cuanto tengamos m√°s novedades, sobre todo ahora con la OP1740.

Un saludo,

Marina PERNAS PEREZ
CAMI Carter Cilindros Valladolid

Confidential C

body:
Hello everyone, 

I‚Äôm sharing this paper which I found very interesting on how to use the Cynefin framework (for complexity management) in an industrial context. It‚Äôs a case study based on a safety analysis in a gold mine, in South Africa. In a nutshell, two key aspects  : a) taking into account the domain of the problem / risk  (‚Äúcomplex‚Äù vs. ‚Äúcomplicated‚Äù domains as defined by this framework) and b) the importance of experimentation in the complex domain (vs. defined Action Plans). 

Comments / feedback welcome !
html_body:
Hello everyone, 

I‚Äôm sharing this paper which I found very interesting on how to use the Cynefin framework (for complexity management) in an industrial context. It‚Äôs a case study based on a safety analysis in a gold mine, in South Africa. In a nutshell, two key aspects  : a) taking into account the domain of the problem / risk  (‚Äúcomplex‚Äù vs. ‚Äúcomplicated‚Äù domains as defined by this framework) and b) the importance of experimentation in the complex domain (vs. defined Action Plans). 

Comments / feedback welcome !

[[tag:31475932]] [[tag:31475933]].1

Hi Sai,
while working on SLDD analysis on CD033, it gave change to identify two issues with the CD033 (v3.1 ) script.
Issue 1: 
There is a condition at Line No : 106 with an elseif condition at Line no:191
if ~isempty(regexp(src_type,'Constant', 'once'))

elseif isempty(regexp(src_type,'Constant', 'once')) 

here elseif doesnot require a condition.

Issue2: 
From an array variable which has multiple elements, only the first element has been chosen for CD033 check. Rest of the elements are ignored. see image for detailed explanation.
html_body:
[[tag:31475932]] [[tag:31475933]].1

elseif isempty(regexp(src_type,'Constant', 'once')) 

here elseif doesnot require a condition.

Issue2: 
From an array variable which has multiple elements, only the first element has been chosen for CD033 check. Rest of the elements are ignored. see image for detailed explanation.

1. For CD042 utility, Currently the script behaviour is designed according to the compilation of the model.
When this has to be removed, the complete flow of the script has to be changed.
If it is so, [[user:1678181442]] support for it is required.
2. I've fixed for the other violations, which are reported.
[[user:1678181442]], check for the 2 outputs in both the excel and in the command window, as per your expectation.
3. ".xls" is changed to .xlsx format.
4. Previously the script was pointing to all the source handles which is consiting of the redunant unit delay --> now script is changed to point to the unit delay
5. Previously the script was pointing to all the constant block, which is duplicate--> now script is changed to point to the unit delay, which is the destination to it.
6. The error message is modified on discussion with [[user:1678181442]] and it is updated in script.
7. s-functions are removed.
8. Warnings in the model during the execution of script, in the command window are removed.
9. As mentioned, For Bus signals it is not handled.
10. ‚Äúlogical(0)‚Äù (resp. ‚Äúlogical(1)‚Äù) is replaced by ‚Äúfalse‚Äù (resp ‚Äútrue‚Äù), in the error message.
html_body:
1. For CD042 utility, Currently the script behaviour is designed according to the compilation of the model.
When this has to be removed, the complete flow of the script has to be changed.
If it is so, [[user:1678181442]] support for it is required.
2. I've fixed for the other violations, which are reported.
[[user:1678181442]], check for the 2 outputs in both the excel and in the command window, as per your expectation.
3. ".xls" is changed to .xlsx format.
4. Previously the script was pointing to all the source handles which is consiting of the redunant unit delay --> now script is changed to point to the unit delay
5. Previously the script was pointing to all the constant block, which is duplicate--> now script is changed to point to the unit delay, which is the destination to it.
6. The error message is modified on discussion with [[user:1678181442]] and it is updated in script.
7. s-functions are removed.
8. Warnings in the model during the execution of script, in the command window are removed.
9. As mentioned, For Bus signals it is not handled.
10. ‚Äúlogical(0)‚Äù (resp. ‚Äúlogical(1)‚Äù) is replaced by ‚Äúfalse‚Äù (resp ‚Äútrue‚Äù), in the error message.

Je vous avais parl√© dans un post pass√© d'un document pour la gestion des choix mati√®res pour les pi√®ces de fixations plastiques.
Le PMR qui signifie : Panel Mati√®res Renault.
Ce document partag√© avec les fournisseurs est remis √† jour tous les ans et cette ann√©e le point marquant et impactant est la disparition du PA 6.6 dans la FONCTION UB15‚Ä¶.
L'alternative pour les nouvelles cr√©ations se porte d√©sormais vers le PA 6 qui a certaines similitudes,
sans rentrer dans les d√©tails on peut √©voquer en √©cart la tenue thermique en pointe qui est de 140¬∞ pour le PA6
versus 150¬∞ pour le PA66.
Le PA6 est un peu plus rigide et pour donner une id√©e de cette diff√©rence si on devait injecter dans un m√™me moule une agrafe ,celle en PA6 donnerait des valeurs de clipsage des tuyaux >10daN alors que nos CDC accepte 5daN maxi.
Ceci est donc pris en  compte lors de la cr√©ation et conception d'une fixation

body:
Dacia Vehicle Plant: New TdC-COGS* War Room

The first TdC-COGS Office Seminar for Dacia Vehicle Plant was organized on 14 March 2019. In the presence of some of the Country Management Committee members were presented levers to achieve the performance and the way to implement the new TdC methodology of the Renault-Nissan-Mitsubishi Alliance.
On this occasion the Dacia Vehicle Plant War Room was inaugurated. The TdC-COGS Office team, consisting of representatives from key jobs (ACO, Engineering, Purchasing, Logistics, Quality, APW, Manufacturing, Finance), presented TOP 4 benchmark analysis, as well as TOP 5 LUP ECO topics for the HJD pivot. 
Christophe Dridi, Groupe Renault Romania General Manager expressed his expectations regarding the achievement of this year's objectives and assured the team that it will have support from the Top Management. 
 
COGS*= Costs of Goods Sales

Vi riporto alcuni commenti di Daniela, che possono essere sicuramente utili alle nostre riflessioni :

Buongiorno a tutti
Grazie innanzi tutto per la bella riunione di ieri che mi √® sembrata proficua.

Se posso aggiungere alla email di Giulia ecco due input che mi sembrano importanti:
A.	in  questi giorni andate a sfogliare, vedere, leggere testate e riviste (possibilmente mensili o settimanali o anche newsletter aziendali) in modo che possiate prendere spunti su come sono organizzati, come sono fatti i titoli, il sommario, gli attacchi degli articoli‚Ä¶ insomma un po' quello che abbiamo visto ieri con Elisa.

B.	La prossima volta, oltre che a confermare la redazione e le macro aree di base, sarebbe utile definire il file rouge dei singoli contenuti e degli articoli. 

Mi spiego meglio: ieri per esempio tornando in treno a Milano ho dato una letta al giornale che si trova nelle carrozze. C‚Äôera un tema ricorrente che √® il viaggio in treno e che ripercorreva in tutti gli articoli.
Nell‚Äôarea istituzionale per esempio si presentavano i treni, le locomotrici, i vagoni etc..
Nell‚Äôintervista c‚Äôera la storia di una campionessa italiana di snowboard che raccontava che a lei piace molto viaggiare e che spesso usa il treno‚Ä¶
Nell‚Äôarea leisure c‚Äôera una sorta di giro delle bellezze italiane e dei monumenti che si possono visitare in treno‚Ä¶
Insomma il concetto base il tema del viaggio in treno era l‚Äôelemento che ‚Äúteneva insieme‚Äù il racconto di tutta la testata, cos√¨ chi legge non si perde e non deve fare lo sforzo per capire la direzione.

Nel nostro caso per esempio il tema dell‚ÄôInnovazione potrebbe essere il filo conduttore per cui:
area istituzionale ÔÉ† come si √® mossa RCi in questa direzione negli ultimi anni, o come intende fare nei prossimi anni
area intervista ÔÉ† un collega o un dipartimento che ha fatto dell‚Äôinnovazione l‚Äôasse importante della sua attivit√†
area engagement ÔÉ† una App o una tecnologia che riporta a questa direzione
area life ÔÉ† un evento aziendale, anche di una filiale estera, di riferimento all‚Äôinnovazione non necessariamente tecnologica ma anche di approccio al business o alle relazioni interne fra i dipartimenti

Chiaramente √® un input che non vuole limitare la direzione che vorrete prendere nei singoli contenuti, ma √® uno stimolo a trovare una strada univoca dei vari articoli che crea omogeneit√†.

Ci vediamo settimana prossima e buon lavoro a tutti.

body:
Como vimos en el I F√≥rum RSIE de 2019, un Producto Digital como los que RSIE debe proporcionar debe basarse en siete principios tecnol√≥gicos. Aqu√≠ caben m√°s palabras que en el F√≥rum, o sea que ponemos algunas pistas m√°s, por si alguien quiere profundizar o aportar sus conocimientos o experiencia sobre el asunto.
 
La Arquitectura Orientada a Web (WOA), elegida y promovida inicialmente por los l√≠deres actuales del mercado (Google, Amazon, Facebook, Apple) ya ha demostrado su eficiencia y flexibilidad como herramienta de contacto con el usuario final de los servicios ofrecidos.
 
Esta manera de hacer las cosas utiliza un conjunto de protocolos y est√°ndares ya maduros (HTTP/HTTPS/XML/JSON/HTML5‚Ä¶) que se apoyan en un API REST y constituyen un entorno desacoplado que permite proporcionar soluciones abiertas, flexibles y robustas con una experiencia de usuario mejorada.
 
Esta definici√≥n es bastante gen√©rica pero enmarca los componentes t√©cnicos de la arquitectura, ya que estandariza:Los mecanismos de distribuci√≥n de la informaci√≥n (HTTP, message driven, publicaci√≥n/suscripci√≥n‚Ä¶).La agregaci√≥n de la informaci√≥n (mashups (ejemplos: GMaps+craigslist, Twitter+GMaps, emoji+twitter, mapas+enfermedades, hazte tu una para ti), hiperenlaces) a trav√©s de API p√∫blicas o privadas.La gesti√≥n de la seguridad (OpenID, HTTPS, SSL, ).La portabilidad de los datos (XML/JSON).La representaci√≥n de los datos (JSON, API REST).Los m√©todos de transferencia de informaci√≥n (API REST, HTTPS‚Ä¶)
 
Como podemos constatar ahora mismo, cada vez hay menos herramientas de instalar y m√°s aplicaciones web. Gmail, Facebook, Amazon, SharePoint‚Ä¶ no existe una versi√≥n de escritorio porque los est√°ndares WOA permiten hacer cosas que hasta hace poco eran impensables en un navegador (adem√°s, la expresi√≥n hace poco cada vez representa un espacio de tiempo menor) y adem√°s eran incompatibles con la estrategia mobile first.
 
Los siguientes patrones se pueden ver ya como algo normal en la Intern√©:Aplicaciones responsivas que adaptan los contenidos al dispositivo que se est√° utilizando, para optimizar la experiencia del usuario.Aplicaciones Web Progresivas que incorporan caracter√≠sticas hasta ahora reservadas a las versiones de escritorio.Ergonom√≠a e Interfaz de Usuario enriquecido, hasta hace unos a√±os atado a inventos como Flash (difunto), applets Java (RIP) o Silverlight (que Microsoft lo tenga en su gloria). Y no, Adobe AIR nunca lleg√≥ a ser una opci√≥n.Single Page Applications, que permiten disfrazar las aplicaciones web para que el usuario no perciba que su app favorita es, en realidad, una aplicaci√≥n web. (Qu√≠tale la barra de direcciones a una SPA y no podr√°s distinguirla de una aplicaci√≥n de escritorio).Mashups que agregan informaci√≥n de fuentes diversas para obtener valor de gratis, y que de momento nosotros resolvemos con exporto aqu√≠, exporto all√°, junto los dos excel, y tres millones de BUSCARV despu√©s‚Ä¶.consecuencias de la monolitiquez) combinando la informaci√≥n de distintos or√≠genes.
 
Por todo esto, la Arquitectura Orientada a Web es un principio fundamental en la creaci√≥n de Productos Digitales.¬†

body:
Hello Victor-Hugo,

I fully understand the needs of our colleagues to automate certain annoying tasks in the daily work. I would like to satisfy this category of needs (RDA) as well. But we also have to differ the needs, the self-service in my humble opinion is RDA (robotic desktop automation), rather than enterprise RPA. And currently our priority (within our ressources) is to stablize first the automation as a service to ensure that will be in a good shape.

Keep in touch.

Best regards,
Xuanjie

https://www.greencarcongress.com/2019/03/20190315-kei.html

Nissan and Mitsubishi to launch new kei cars as collaboration expands; semiautonomous technology

15 March 2019

Nissan Motor Co., Ltd. and Mitsubishi Motors Corporation will introduce four new minivehicles in Japan through their joint venture, as the companies continue to expand their collaboration.

Production of the all-new Nissan Dayz, Nissan Dayz Highway Star, Mitsubishi eK wagon and Mitsubishi eK X has begun at Mitsubishi‚Äôs Mizushima Plant in Kurashiki, Japan. For the first time, the models will be offered with semiautonomous driving technology, designed for single-lane use on highways.

NMKV, a joint venture of the two companies, integrated Nissan‚Äôs advanced technologies and Mitsubishi‚Äôs extensive experience in minivehicle production into the tall wagon-type cars.

The companies launched the first generation of the models in 2013 and have increased their collaboration since becoming Alliance partners in 2016. Last month, the all-new Nissan Livina, which shares a platform with the Mitsubishi Xpander, went on sale in Indonesia.

The new models deliver a markedly improved performance, with upgraded platforms, engines and transmissions. They also feature all-new design. While the Nissan and Mitsubishi minivehicles share key components, they retain separate brand features.

The models will go on sale later this month.

body:
Facts & Moves - March 20th 2019
(Full note attached below)

‚Ä¢	KEY POINTS: Fed to confirm pause
Today‚Äôs key event is the monetary policy council of the Fed (FOMC) tonight. Markets are widely expecting no change in Fed Fund rates with the Fed maintaining a patient stance. But the overall aspects of the Fed meeting could be dovish, including a more subdued growth outlook (i.e. downward revision of economic projections ‚Äì a modest one is expected) and lower dot plot trajectory (i.e. rate hike profile in 2019 and 2020). Recent USD weakness arguably reflects such expectations for a dovish outcome, with market participants likely focused on a lowering of the dots. While the Fed is currently expecting 2 rate hikes in 2019 and 1 in 2020, a shift in the median dot to signal one hike for 2019 and none for 2020 may not drive the USD much lower. There should also be more explicit guidance on balance sheet policy (perhaps informally in the press conference rather than a statement) that signals an end to balance sheet shrinkage later this year. Note that any further shift in tone or signalling from Powell should influence the USD (EUR/USD at 1.1354 at the time of writing). 
Separately, US-China trade relations were back in focus yesterday, as reputable sources seemed to convey contradictory messages on the state of ongoing negotiations. Bloomberg cited sources indicating that it appeared as though China were ‚Äústepping back‚Äù on trade pledges, whereas the Wall Street Journal quoted sources indicating that talks were in final stages. Executive vice president of the US Chamber of Commerce Myron Brilliant was quoted as saying ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre in the endgame‚Äù. The market appears to be siding with the more positive view (i.e. limiting USD strengthening). US Trade Representative Robert Lighthizer and Treasury Secretary Steve Mnuchin are scheduled to travel to Beijing next week for further talks.  

ALSO of interest today: UK (Britain's messy divorce continues, inflation rate), Australia ( Minutes of the RBA), Argentina (ARS), Poland (industrial production, wages)

body:
Thanks [[user:1678571686]]. Please update the latest version in dimensions.

For your point on Compilation. CD042 script or the Utility: It doesnot need for the compilation because in order to evaluate the string parameter defined in the Init Value attribute of the Unit Delay Blocks, there is no need of compiling the model.

we are using the Init_val = evalin('base',Init_cond); other than this there are no compiled port datatypes/portwidths,dimensions, etc that need compilation are present.

The only thing needed is the existence of the parameter in the workspace. Let me know your point on this.
html_body:
Thanks [[user:1678571686]]. Please update the latest version in dimensions.

For your point on Compilation. CD042 script or the Utility: It doesnot need for the compilation because in order to evaluate the string parameter defined in the Init Value attribute of the Unit Delay Blocks, there is no need of compiling the model.

body:
1)	Purpose: verification of the tightening torque for the assembly screws of the ASM and cushion side members.
2 cars analysed:
-	VIN VF1HJD20060705263, ~ 11 000  km
-	VIN VF1HJD40958884030, ~ 17 000  km

2)	Method: 
ÔÉò	set the dynamometric wrench on 7.2 Nm ( minimum tightening torque that is specified by Martur);
ÔÉò	put a red marking on the head of the screw and the metal sheet in order to set the initial position;
ÔÉò	put the wrench on the screw and tighten towards 7.2 Nm. If the marking remains on the initial position, the minimum torque is assured. If the marking moves, the minimum torque is not assured.
ÔÉò	Verification made only on the drivers seats.

3)	Conclusions of the analysis:
ÔÉò	VIN VF1HJD20060705263, ~ 11 000 km
-	All the 4 screws were under 7.2 Nm. The screw was rotating starting from 5.8 Nm, therefore the minimum torque is not maintained ( see pictures 4&5, video_1)
-	Info: efforts label from the frame ok.

ÔÉò	VIN VF1HJD40958884030,  ~ 17 000 km
-	1  screw ( interior front side) was under 7.2 Nm. The screw was rotating starting from 6 Nm, therefore the minimum torque is not respected ( see picture 6 & video_2)
-	Info: the print on the efforts label from the frame was erased.

Things get much better when people work together, consult and help each other.
