Hola a todos, en el sharepoint de la Direcci√≥n Financiera he colgado el informe con los resultados de la √∫ltima encuesta a los empleados de nuestra direcci√≥n.

En primer lugar, agradeceros a todos los que hab√©is contribuido con vuestras aportaciones al plan de acci√≥n, porque hemos conseguido mejorar la valoraci√≥n en 6 puntos, tanto en Compromiso como en Soporte Organizativo.

Varios aspectos muestran una evoluci√≥n favorable y en algunos aspectos estamos incluso por encima de los valores de referencia del global RENAULT ESPA√ëA, como por ejemplo: la relaci√≥n entre mi trabajo y los objetivos generales de la empresa, las condiciones materiales de trabajo (instalaciones, espacios‚Ä¶), la autonom√≠a suficiente para hacer mi trabajo‚Ä¶

Sin embargo, lejos de complacernos con la evoluci√≥n, hay aspectos que se han degradado (p.e. el inter√©s real de tu direcci√≥n por la vida laboral de sus empleados) y otros que, aunque hayan mejorado, siguen mostrando valores muy bajos cuando nos comparamos con otros compa√±eros de RESA (p.e. la organizaci√≥n del trabajo favorece la calidad del mismo, la compa√±√≠a me motiva para contribuir m√°s all√° de lo que requiere mi trabajo, la confianza en tu direcci√≥n‚Ä¶).

Por otro lado, agradecer tambi√©n los comentarios a aquellos que los hab√©is transmitido en la encuesta y que reflejan de manera mayoritaria una preocupaci√≥n por los √∫tiles inform√°ticos, procesos inadecuados, posibilidades de estandarizaci√≥n y automatizaci√≥n‚Ä¶

Seguiremos trabajando en 2019 para conseguir entre todos mejorar el entorno de trabajo de la D Financiera de RESA y reafirmar nuestro compromiso.

body:
Le collage des joints PART 2.

Pour bien positionner sur caisse ou sur porte le joint dans un process manuel , il est important de proc√©der avec m√©thode et r√©gularit√©.

Pour rappel un joint est r√©alis√© chez les fournisseurs √† partir d'une machine complexe et tr√®s longue ( 200m) en fin de ligne, on y assemble l'adh√©sif et  d√©coupe a longueur le joint en fin de process pour ensuite √™tre livr√© en usine de montage dans un conditionnement droit. (pas de courbure ni de plis)
Nota: l'adh√©sif est double face , il est coll√© sur le joint avec un CDC pr√©cis  et livr√© avec un "LINER" (protection de l'adh√©sif)  pour √™tre coll√© sur nos v√©hicules. 

Lors de la pose manuelle, le joint √† l'√©tat repos est par d√©finition "extensible" si l'on d√©cide  de l'√©tendre comme un √©lastique.

il y a tout de m√™me des limites , car dans le profil du joint ,un fil conducteur r√©duit consid√©rablement cette "extention"  possible.
N√©anmoins dans notre process et avec des longueurs de joint cons√©quentes , il √† √©t√© possible de retrouver une sur-longueur non n√©gligeable. (20/25 mm sur 2 m√®tres de joint (ex J92)
A partir du moment ou le joint est coll√© avec un √©tirement croissant au fur et a mesure de son accostage (coll√© sur la porte ou la caisse) et de son collage (avec pression)  il demandera toujours √† revenir en position "z√©ro" d'ou les d√©collements fr√©quents en bout de joint ou bien en pleine courbure.

La temp√©rature joue aussi un r√¥le important.
lors de la pose:
un joint dans un environnement froid sera plus "r√©tract√©" lors de sa mise en place et de son collage. Lors de la mont√©e en temp√©rature, sans intervention ext√©rieure, il reprend sa forme normale ce qui forcement fait varier sa longueur et donc il se d√©colle.
Dans un environnement "chaud" ( au del√† de 30¬∞/35¬∞) le joint est dans sa forme finale il suffit simplement de na pas l'√©tirer.

Diff√©rents "jigs" permettent de guider l'op√©rateur pour le bon positionnement du joint sur porte ou caisse.
Avec les nums il est important de r√©aliser d√®s le d√©part un outil simple, non contraignant et r√©p√©table pour garantir le bon positionnement du joint.
mais comme cela reste une op√©ration "manuelle" le risque z√©ro n'existe pas.

Un op√©rateur form√© √† la mise en place du joint par le biais du DOJO Collage  permet de r√©duire consid√©rablement le risque de d√©collement du joint lors de sa pose.

en partie 3 je parlerai du collage du joint avec les 2 processus connu chez RSA.

√† la semaine prochaine.
Dominique

Dans un environnement "chaud" ( au del√† de 30¬∞/35¬∞) le joint est dans sa forme finale il suffit simplement de na pas l'√©tirer.

Diff√©rents "jigs" permettent de guider l'op√©rateur pour le bon positionnement du joint sur porte ou caisse.
Avec les nums il est important de r√©aliser d√®s le d√©part un outil simple, non contraignant et r√©p√©table pour garantir le bon positionnement du joint.
mais comme cela reste une op√©ration "manuelle" le risque z√©ro n'existe pas.

Un op√©rateur form√© √† la mise en place du joint par le biais du DOJO Collage  permet de r√©duire consid√©rablement le risque de d√©collement du joint lors de sa pose.

en partie 3 je parlerai du collage du joint avec les 2 processus connu chez RSA.

√† la semaine prochaine.

body: - Smile at Work ! -Living under a routine, we can easily be in a zombie-like state when coming into work. We zip into work quickly following the same routines we‚Äôve habituated. Our target is to get to work, and we can sometimes forget about the people around us, in other cubes/offices/departments. So, the challenge is to practice beaming with smile as you come into work. Smile genuinely with people you meet. Be completely pleased to see them. Make it a focus for the day, to bring more happiness into the lives of others. Ask them genuinely and infused with energy, ‚ÄúHow are ya?‚Äù ‚ÄúHow was your weekend?‚Äù Watch the smiles surface on their face.

Ivan & Thomas.

body:
Announcement for PAMCRASH users !!!  
In order to optimize HPC Intermediate Storage usage and to avoid the overload of EDC, at the end of a PAMCRASH simulation, the DSY file backup on SI is replaced with the backup of its femzipped version (DSY.fz file). 

Introduced at RENAULT 5 years ago, FEMZIP is a smart compression tool developped to reduce by about a factor of 10 the size of the PAMCRASH DSY file while keeping the most relevant information. 
Post-processing tools like METAPOST are designed to support the compressed data format of FEMZIP. 
Additional information are available on the web FEMZIP site : http://www.sidact.com/femzip-crash.html.

Buna tuturor,

Pentru ca ne dorim ca toti colegii care au fost inscrisi la platforma SC Academy, sa reuseasca sa termine modulele, in cele 12 luni pe care le au la dispozitie (licenta fiind disponibila 12 luni din momentul inscrierii), am deschis un fisier in care sa notati data la care acestia sa inceapa efectiv trainingul.

Clemanta BACIU, pentru ca doar ea poate administra accesul la platforma, va tine cont de aceasta data, care va reprezenta startul formarii propriu-zise si momentul in care incepe scadenta licentei.

In acest scop va rog sa va consultati cu colegii dvoastra si sa documentati data cea mai potrivita pentru debut formare (01.mm.2019) - deadline 8 aprilie.

Mult spor.

GIlles Brousson, arquitecto de seguridad, nos recuerda las usos para los que esta pensado Teleservices y para los que no:

 Il est interdit √† un prestataires ext√©rieur de se connecter en VPN ou autre solution comme Teamviewer directement dans l'intranet Renault.
 
 Pour effectuer des t√¢ches de support exceptionnelles, qui demande la connexion ou la visualisation sur des √©quipements donn√©s suite √† un incident, la solution est le t√©l√©service.
 
 Le t√©l√©service ne donne pas le droit de faire n'importe quoi dans l'intranet. Il doit se faire suite √† un incident, et l'intervenant doit √™tre suivi par le demandeur Renault. Ce n'est donc pas un droit √† se promener dans l'intranet.
 
 Le transfert de fichier est en effet impossible car interdit. C'est √† la personne Renault demandeur de l'ouverture d'incident de se charger de cette gestion des fichiers.

body:
Data Driven¬†hace referencia al uso de datos para la toma de decisiones. Este concepto no es nuevo, pero la evoluci√≥n de la tecnolog√≠a que ha hecho posible almacenar datos que antes s√≥lo imagin√°bamos que exist√≠an, s√≠.

Lo anterior ha hecho que el asset principal en la era de la Transformaci√≥n Digital sea, precisamente, el dato. Una vez recogido y almacenado, puede ser tratado para generar m√∫ltiples informaciones que ayuden a la toma de decisiones de cualquier actividad o negocio.

Cuando el volumen de datos es suficientemente grande y diverso, hablamos de BigData; concepto tras el que normalmente encontramos herramientas espec√≠ficas as√≠ como un sistema de gesti√≥n de datos que permite:
Almacenar gran volumen de datos de todo tipoAnalizar de forma transversal cualquier conjunto de datosOfrecer a cada cada usuario los datos que realmente le hacen falta (sin las restricciones habituales de los Data Warehouses tradicionales)Ejecutar todo lo anterior con el mejor nivel de rendimiento

Las actividades anteriores requieren conocimientos t√©cnicos y coordinaci√≥n. Los nuevos actores involucrados son:
Data Owner: define el dato y sus atributos (normalmente en el lado business)Data Steward: ayuda al business en la definici√≥n del dato y es el responsable de la aplicaci√≥n donde se generan los datos, as√≠ como de su carga (ingesta) en el sistema bigdataData Engineer: desarrolla los tratamientos de los datos (formateado, calculos, cruces‚Ä¶)Data Analyst: los analistas exploran los datos y proponen formas de visualizarlos de forma que sean m√°s comprensibles y as√≠ facilitar la toma de decisionesData Scientist: tambi√©n explora los datos, pero su objetivo es elaborar algoritmos que permitan predecir comportamientos/resultados, apoy√°ndose muchas veces en la Inteligencia Artificial

Si nos centramos en Reanult, y c√≥mo hace la gesti√≥n de su BigData, encontramos que la soluci√≥n elegida pasa por construir un Datalake apoy√°ndose en Hadoop, y en un proceso que permite preparar los datos antes utilizarlos. En este proceso para llegar al Datalake los datos pasan por tres estados:
Transit: cuando los datos llegan y est√°n pendientes de cargaRaw: datos cargados en formato brutoGold: a partir de los datos brutos, se pueden ejecutar tratamientos para adecuar los datos a las necesidades particulares, esos tratamientos pueden incluir filtros, agregaciones, cruces de datos, o c√°lculos para obtener datos derivados

Como resultado, los usuarios pueden utilizar herramientas de consulta y visualizaci√≥n de datos para hacer reporting, o pueden construirse nuevos sistemas que permitan integrar decisiones en los procesos del negocio de forma m√°s din√°mica.

Pero... y eso que tiene que ver con un Producto Digital Data Driven. Bien, √©sta caracter√≠stica tambi√©n hace referencia al uso de datos para la toma de decisiones, pero en este caso relacionadas con la evoluci√≥n del producto: i.e.:
¬øes una funcionalidad tan importante o cr√≠tica como pensamos?¬øes necesario evolucionar una funcionalidad pero no estamos seguros de si tendr√° el impacto imaginado?¬øcu√°l es el uso real del producto?¬øC√≥mo se comporta el producto en la infraestructura que lo tiene alojado?

Conocer el comportamiento de los usuarios frente a una aplicaci√≥n, su forma de navegar, el tiempo que pasa en determinadas pantallas, el consumo de memoria de ciertos servicios en determinadas ocasiones, el n√∫mero de usuarios que diariamente se conecta y en qu√© momentos del d√≠a lo hace, etc... puede ayudar a evolucionar lo realmente necesario y a evitar problemas e incidentes. consiguiendo usuarios m√°s satisfechos y mejores resultados para el negocio.

Las t√©cnicas para la colecta de estas informaciones en nuestros sistemas suelen ser sencillas, ir incluyendo marcas de paso por determinados sitios y de esta forma registrar llamadas a servicios. Para la parte front-end de las aplicaciones, Renault ha elegido Matomo (que adem√°s de permitir el seguimiento de los puntos de paso de un usuario) ofrece un interfaz para analizar mejor los comportamientos.

Para los que est√©is interesados en profundizar en estos temas, os dejo un v√≠deo que explica los conceptos anteriores y algunos otros enlaces interesantes:
Video en franc√©s: linkVideo en ingl√©s: linkInformaci√≥n en Confluence sobre los procesos asociados a la carga y consulta de datalake: linkTutoriales para aprender a usarlo: linkTutoriales para los que quieran probar an√°lisis con Lenguaje R: linkExplorador de tablas y datos disponibles en datalake, organizado por categor√≠as, aplicaciones, procesos... : linkPresentaci√≥n sobre c√≥mo usar Matomo en Renault: aqu√≠

¬°Buena lectura!

Dear colleagues,

As you all know, we are currently in the middle of the Salon de Promotion. This coming Sunday the 24th of March, some of our dealerships will be open.

Instead of a traditional Easter OPO, we will hold a sales activation in the month of April. On Easter Monday (22nd of April), many of our dealerships will organize a special Easter opening.

You can find an overview of the dealerships that are open this Sunday or on Easter Monday at the following location:
I:\NL\Public\Renault - RCI\OPO zondagsopeningen

To get an idea of the local activities initiated by our dealers, we would like to advise and encourage you to visit one or more locations either during the OPO or on Easter Monday (or better still ‚Äì both!). 
If you plan on making a visit, please fill this in on the Excel file to ensure we have a good spread between locations.

If I forgot to include a colleague or you want to forward this to your team, please feel free.

Thanks in advance!

Met vriendelijke groet, with kind regards, cordialement,

Stevie KIEL-CLAYTON
Co√∂rdinator Dealercommunication

body:
Hello everybody,

Thanks again for your time for this new training sessions about Facebook and the Lead Notification. Please find attached the training support and below the participants list.

Regarding the question raised yesterday about the email notification sent through the notification center when the prospect didn't give his agreement: we had the feedback of the GDPR Corporate team. It's a notification of the good delivery of the request, without commercial offer, in the context of the purpose of the request (test drive request, etc.). It's therefore GDPR compliant.

There is a mistake on the training document about the Facebook lead parameter: the origin field must be "social-paid" and not "Facebook". The step by step document available on SharePoint is correct.

Regards,

Laurent & Adrien

body:
Facts & Moves - March 21st 2019
(Full note attached below)

‚Ä¢	KEY POINTS: Dovish Fed surprise 
Finally, the Fed turned extremely dovish overnight. J. Powell, Governor of the Fed, announced no planned interest rate hikes for 2019 (from two previously), which sent the USD down nearly 1% against the euro, breaking through the 1.1448 level for the first time since early Feb. They now only expect one more hike in 2020. The Fed acknowledged the recent softening of the growth and inflation outlook. The updated FOMC statement noted that incoming data showed that ‚Äúgrowth of economic activity has slowed from its solid rate in the fourth quarter‚Äù. The Fed‚Äôs adjusted rate hike plans have encouraged the market to speculate that the Fed is close to the end of their rate hike cycle, and that the next move may even be a rate cut perhaps even as soon as late this year. The downward pressure on US yields continues to support the outlook for a weaker USD this year.
More explicit guidance on their balance sheet plans was also delivered. The Fed indicated the pace of redemptions would slow from May and that the shrinking of the balance sheet will end in Sept. In particular the pace of redemptions, currently capped at USD 30bn for US Treasuries (UST) and USD 20bn for Mortgage-backed securities (MBS) will begin to slow but only for US Treasuries, to USD 15bn per month, from May. After the aggregate balance sheet reduction stops in Sept., the FOMC has indicated that proceeds from redemptions of MBS (the pace of which looks set to continue at the current rate) will be re-invested in US Treasuries. Although the aggregate securities portfolio of the Fed will persist at roughly USD 3.7 trillion, the composition will shift more to US Treasuries (and seeking to replicate the existing maturity profile). 
Following Fed‚Äôs announcements, the USD weakened somewhat (but recovered since then to 1.1347). The JPY and EM currencies (especially commodities-related currencies which also benefit from higher commodity prices ‚Äì notably RUB, ZAR, MXN) strengthened.
Regarding the state of ongoing discussions between US and China, we were mentioning yesterday that reputable sources seemed to convey contradictory messages. There was a major news overnight highlighting a presumed hardening of President Trump‚Äôs position vis-√†-vis China. He said that the customs surcharges would remain in place until Washington is sure that Beijing respects the trade agreements that have been concluded. If Lighthizer/Mnuchin go to Beijing next week, that‚Äôs a good sign it was verbal jockeying.

ALSO of interest today: UK (extension request of Th. May), Switzerland, Norway, Indonesia (monetary policy council), Australia (employment data), Russia (retail sales), Poland (construction output), Hungary and Brazil (politics), brent

body:
Hi [[user:1640205200]] 
1. The script should check if the initial condition for both/N unit delays (eg. abc - a string) . If they are same then their values will also be same in base workspace and if they are different (eg. abc and def) then it is not redundant. 
2. If abc =2 and def =2 then also they are not redundant. But here already the strings are different we donot need to check base workspace.
3. if one unit delay is '0' and other as 'abc' then also they are not redundant (eventhough abc value is 0) this is not compliant with CD046 magic numbers in AMBDR.

There might still be more patterns. What i mean is we compare the string if that is same then redundant unit delay is present else not present. Currently script checks for the value of the string and fails point 2. And Nan issue also.
html_body:

1. The script should check if the initial condition for both/N unit delays (eg. abc - a string) . If they are same then their values will also be same in base workspace and if they are different (eg. abc and def) then it is not redundant. 
2. If abc =2 and def =2 then also they are not redundant. But here already the strings are different we donot need to check base workspace.
3. if one unit delay is '0' and other as 'abc' then also they are not redundant (eventhough abc value is 0) this is not compliant with CD046 magic numbers in AMBDR.

There might still be more patterns. What i mean is we compare the string if that is same then redundant unit delay is present else not present. Currently script checks for the value of the string and fails point 2. And Nan issue also.

body:
Solution:
we may create a Matlab function which will be called in individual mchecks which are using evalin "base" logic.
1.This function will first check the variable exists in model workspace.
2.If not, then it will check whether model is linked to Simulink Data Dictionary. 
3.If it is linked to DD then it will evaluate the variable from DD otherwise it will try to evaluate the variable in Base workspace.
4.If the variable doesnot exist in all the cases. it will check whether the value 
is being called from Mask Workspace and generate the output.
html_body:
Solution:
we may create a Matlab function which will be called in individual mchecks which are using evalin "base" logic.
1.This function will first check the variable exists in model workspace.
2.If not, then it will check whether model is linked to Simulink Data Dictionary. 
3.If it is linked to DD then it will evaluate the variable from DD otherwise it will try to evaluate the variable in Base workspace.
4.If the variable doesnot exist in all the cases. it will check whether the value 
is being called from Mask Workspace and generate the output.

body:
Buna ziua,

In data de 30 octombrie 2018 am semnalat pentru prima data problemele privind spatiul redus pentru picioare al noilor autocare si scaunele incomode (fiind vorba initial de B-319-DLS, naveta de Lujerului-CTT, ulterior s-a constatat ca problema este generalizata pe intreaga flota)
Dupa multe mail-uri, s-a marit spatiul pt picioare cu aproximativ 2cm, bineinteles, total insuficienti.

Recent am relansat problema si pe data de 20 februarie 2019 ati anuntat ca va avea loc un audit. Pe 14 martie am lasat un comentariu sa va intreb care sunt rezultatele acestui audit si nu am avut niciun raspuns. 

Insist, din nou, sa va cer rezultatele acestui audit (daca a fost realizat) si care este planul de actiune pentru a corecta eventualele probleme intalnite, cu responsabili si termene limita pentru implementare.

Problemele sunt semnalate de aproape 5 luni si nu am vazut nici o actiune semnificativa.

O zi buna in continuare

body:
"Using encryption" doesn't say all ! 
For instance many Office products use encryption, but only for the transport over internet *which is ofcourse good), but once on the infra of MS it is decrypted.
Using end-to-end encryption (client-to-client) is better. WhatsApe has this, but then it is said there is a backdoor (for US Gov). Such a backdoor can be used by others too.

And more over WhatsApp is a disaster for privacy. It sends your addressbook and keeps track of everything you do (if you have badly configured also your locations) to a central server.

Google a little around on internet and you see what we mean.

En pratique, selon les derni√®res √©tudes d'IDC, les professionnels de la donn√©e passent en moyenne moins de 20% de leur temps √† analyser r√©ellement les informations mises √† leur disposition. Le reste est occup√© par des t√¢ches sans r√©elle valeur ajout√©e : recherche, pr√©paration ou gouvernance des donn√©es.
 
 Beaucoup reste donc √† faire dans l‚Äôexploitation des donn√©es, dans l‚Äôautomatisation de leur recherche, de leur pr√©paration‚Ä¶ Surtout que de nouvelles r√©glementations, comme le GDPR, n‚Äôam√©liorent pas la situation, augmentant le temps pass√© en pr√©paration de donn√©es. S'y ajoutent les complexit√©s li√©es aux organisations elles-m√™mes, qui doivent apprivoiser un nouveau sujet par essence transversal. En moyenne, les professionnels de la donn√©e perdent 10 heures par semaine √† travailler sur des sujets d√©j√† explor√©s par d'autres, au sein m√™me de leur entreprise.
 
 ‚Ä¢ Comment organiser les activit√©s de traitement et de valorisation de la donn√©e ?
 ‚Ä¢ Quels environnements technologiques sont les plus propices √† la ma√Ætrise du capital informationnel ?
 ‚Ä¢ Quels leviers actionner pour casser les silos internes ?
 ‚Ä¢ O√π sont les gisements de valeur les plus imm√©diats permettant de justifier les strat√©gies Big Data ?
 
 Autant de questions sur lesquelles se penchera la conf√©rence ¬´ Gouvernance de la donn√©e ¬ª d'IDC France le 06 juin 2019.

Ana Maria, ar fi extraordinar sa reuseasca. Nu vad de ce nu se poate aplica si in Romania aceeasi relaxare a politicii de teletravail ca si in Franta unde toti sunt incurajati sa aiba 2 zile de teletravail INDIFERENT de nivelul ierarhic. Pana la urma se reduce la maturitatea echipelor de a respecta niste reguli simple si la increderea managementului. Pana acum , nu am auzit de derapaje in teletravail. 
De asemenea , indiferent de functie de management sau nu, manager de echipa sau nu, toti trebuie sa aiba acest drept. De ce managerul sa stea la birou cand echipa lui este in teletravail. La ce ajuta?
Cred ca asta ar fi intr-adevar o noua regula in casa noua care va fi apreciata la toate nivelurile la justa valoare. In acelasi timp si cei care sunt edezavantajati de aceasta mutare vor fi mai motivati si mai linistiti......

body:
CHASSIS ACTIVITY IN DACIA POWERTRAIN & CHASSIS PLANT REACHES TARGET OF ENTERING THE "EXCELLENCE GROUP"

At the end of February, the PHC (Plant Health Check) audit was conducted by DQSC and APW for the activity of chassis manufacturing, on the machining, welding and assembly lines.
Compared to the January 2018 audit, the process scoring progresses to 4,5 (vs. 4,2) and the product scoring improves to 4,3 (vs. 3,8).
The good application of daily animation standards, the use of help call by all operators and the very effective polyvalence management were highlighted at the end of the audit. Also, the auditors have identified opportunities for improvements such as OPT effectiveness with gaps or improvement ideas, action plans oriented on prevention and more depth in analyzes, same level of rigor requirements on the visualization and 5S for all the workshops.
This performance is the result of teamwork in recent years between manufacturing and all support functions. The challenge is to remain in this group, like Engines, and the Aluminum and Gearboxes departments to enter during October and December audits.
Congratulations to our colleagues for this performance!

body: Yesterday was the 3rd workshop of the Chapter ABA Supply Chain Renault team. We did the retrospective after 6 months of our chapter life, worked on the chapter maturity assesment axis, shared our chapter Identity card and proposed some KPIs to measure our chapter performance. Thanks to the good spirit and dynamism of the team, we identified a lot of ideas and actions that will help us reach the objectives of our chapter. We also had some fun around big (!!) pizzas. Congratulation and many thanks to all the team and to our helpful coach, Pierre.

body:
HR10DET TDC SEMINARY AT DACIA POWERTRAIN & CHASSIS PLANT
On 12 and 13 March, the HR10DET TDC Seminary was organized, attended by representatives of all professions from Romania, Corporate France and other Alliance factories.
In order to achieve the wanted results, the participants studied the possibilities of cost optimization and analyzed the transformation value and the opportunity to make or buy certain components.
They also compared the HR10 engine with the H4 engine and similar engines produced by Volkswagen, Ford or Kia.
In the end, 83 new ideas emerged that will be applied in the coming period.
"Thank you for your significant contribution. The key to success is the speed at which we make concrete as many as possible of the ideas you found during these 2 days " said Christophe Dridi, General Manager of Dacia and General Manager of Groupe Renault Romania.

body:
Facts & Moves - March 22nd 2019
(Full note attached below)

‚Ä¢	KEY POINTS: New Brexit date while EZ growth loses momentum again 
Brexit will not happen on March 29th. Overnight, the European Council has agreed to give UK an extension until May 22nd to pass the legislation that would implement Brexit, provided the Withdrawal Agreement is approved by the House of Commons next week. However, if the Withdrawal Agreement is not approved by the House of Commons next week (the probability seems high), the European Council agrees to an extension until April 12th and expects the United Kingdom to indicate a way forward before this date for consideration by the European Council. 
Globally, by postponing Brexit day by at least a fortnight, the UK and the EU have kept all options in play, for now. The UK can: 1) Leave the EU with the Prime Minister‚Äôs current Brexit deal on 22 May; 2) Choose by 12 April to leave the EU with ‚Äúno deal‚Äù; 3) Seek a long Brexit delay (in order to organize a 2nd referendum, general elections, etc.) and field candidates for the European elections; 4) Unilaterally revoke Article 50. Short Brexit delay provided fleeting pound relief (EUR/GBP at 0.8566 at the time of writing, appreciating by 1.3%). 
After Brexit EU leaders discussed today on industrial and trade policies. The subject is crucial, as the Eurozone economy lost momentum again in March. According to preliminary estimate released today, March composite PMI fell to 51.3 from 51.9 in Feb. Global activity expanded only modestly as manufacturers reported their steepest downturn for six years (manufacturing PMI at 47.7 from 49.4 in Feb. ‚Äì French and German manufacturing PMI respectively at 49.8 and 44.7) as downturns in factory output and new orders gained momentum. The service sector showed greater resilience but remained in its worst growth spell since late-2016 (services PMI at 52.7 from 52.8 in Feb. ‚Äì French and German services PMI respectively at 48.7 and 54.9). Globally, the Eurozone economy ended the first quarter on a soft note, with the flash PMI running at one of the lowest levels seen since 2014. The survey indicates that GDP likely rose by a modest 0.2% in the opening quarter, with a decline in manufacturing output in the region of 0.5% being offset by an expansion of service sector output of approximately 0.3% (manufacturing accounts for 20% of GDP). Note that growth could even be weaker in Q2-19. As New order growth stagnated for a second successive month following a slight decline in Jan., with backlogs of work dropping for the third time in four months. On the news, the EUR weakened against USD (at 1.1290 at the time of writing), erasing Fed‚Äôs dovish message of this week.

ALSO of interest today: Japan (inflation, manufacturing PMI), Turkey (IMF transcript, political developmentsBCRT announcement), Russia (central bank meeting), Brazil (social security reform and political developments)

BUSINESS TRIP OF STEPHANE VANHOUCKE IN BURSA
This week, we had a great pleasure to welcome Stephane VANHOUCKE , VP Directeur Alliance IT Services  in Bursa. This business trip was a complementary to know DSI Black Sea Organization. It was a very rich day with the presentation of DSI Oyak Renault organization and meeting our organization's members, expecially members of SSC IT Black Sea.  Gemba Digital Manufacturing was so interesting with lots of real use cases on the field. We had as well an opportunity to see the status of our SSC IT Black Sea actions in terms of follow-up. Hope to see you again soon in Black Sea.
